1
00:00:01,290 --> 00:00:09,700
<b>Hotel Del Luna Blu-ray Disc 4</b>
Subtitle re-timing by Jharel

2
00:00:57,516 --> 00:00:59,686
{\an8}Boss, what are you doing out here?

3
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:04,056
{\an8}This place has the nicest view
of the moon.

4
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:08,069
{\an8}Princess Song-hwa is here to see you.

5
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:04,291
Why are you leaving?

6
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:06,166
Didn't you come to the castle to see me?

7
00:02:07,502 --> 00:02:08,502
No.

8
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:10,673
I came to steal.

9
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:12,836
A clumsy man is keeping guard,

10
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:14,724
so I thought it'd be
a great night to steal.

11
00:02:17,179 --> 00:02:19,509
I thought I managed to run into someone
I missed.

12
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,768
But I guess I just ran into a thief.

13
00:02:26,605 --> 00:02:28,065
What did you steal?

14
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:32,316
This belongs to someone I care for.

15
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:37,616
I guess you came to see me yourself
because I didn't show up

16
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,084
while you were drinking.

17
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:40,910
Forget it.

18
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:47,576
It seemed like you were busy
seducing that lady.

19
00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:48,668
You should get going.

20
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:51,384
You saw that?

21
00:02:52,464 --> 00:02:56,434
But did it really seem like
I was the one seducing her?

22
00:02:57,511 --> 00:02:59,471
Clearly, she was the one seducing me.

23
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:03,518
You're one lucky guy.
You even get drinks from someone so noble.

24
00:03:05,394 --> 00:03:06,604
I like this better.

25
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:09,017
And it's more my style.

26
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,280
I'm going to...

27
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:15,025
confiscate this.

28
00:03:17,406 --> 00:03:19,906
It seems like you already stole
what you were here for.

29
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:22,910
So you should go back.

30
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:28,254
The guards are very alert
due to the rebel forces,

31
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,383
so it's very dangerous.

32
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:33,461
I'll pay for the bottle
the next time we meet.

33
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:22,100
At this rate, the tree will soon
be covered with flowers.

34
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:28,516
Chan-sung will put on airs again
when he sees this.

35
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:10,022
He's trying to scare me.

36
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:17,436
<i>Are you enjoying this? I'm hot, aren't I?</i>

37
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:38,514
<i>Are you enjoying this?</i>

38
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:58,232
Out of the way!

39
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:15,503
Hey, what was that guy doing
in the ladies' room?

40
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,125
I don't know. He must be a pervert.

41
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:18,921
The ladies' room?

42
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:32,774
I definitely got the chills.

43
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:35,023
What was it?

44
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:49,624
Is this possessed or something?

45
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:57,999
<i>You're a ghost who's living
inside a human's body, aren't you?</i>

46
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:01,761
<i>Was it your doing?</i>

47
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:14,726
You should be in the afterlife.

48
00:07:14,893 --> 00:07:17,563
This is the punishment
for corrupting the order of this world.

49
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:19,226
You must vanish immediately.

50
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:32,285
It wasn't her doing.

51
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:39,173
She is just a soul
Man-wol has decided to keep alive.

52
00:07:40,377 --> 00:07:42,297
She is not an evil ghost
that has harmed humans.

53
00:07:50,679 --> 00:07:54,389
Why has a lowly ghost taken over a body
and been going around like this?

54
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,604
The owner of the body

55
00:07:55,684 --> 00:07:58,274
died due to the foolish choice
of her parents.

56
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:01,901
Man-wol let her soul live
in an empty body.

57
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:04,782
Strictly speaking,
she has not harmed any human.

58
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:11,531
Man-wol has done a peculiar thing again.

59
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:13,115
Hurry up and leave here.

60
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:24,502
A human was harmed here just now.

61
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:26,337
It's a ghost I have been looking for.

62
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:28,633
It has harmed a human,
so it is an evil ghost.

63
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:31,007
Get rid of it as soon as you catch it.

64
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:32,554
Another Mago has ordered me

65
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:35,636
to find it and put it back
where it used to be.

66
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:37,684
Hotel del Luna again?

67
00:08:37,851 --> 00:08:39,481
It was a guest there.

68
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:42,269
You should capture all of the ghosts
wandering around

69
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:45,525
and take them to the other world instantly
instead of letting them have a rest.

70
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:47,278
Is the path to the other world
an expressway?

71
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,900
Why do they need a rest area?

72
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,492
Why did she have to create such a thing

73
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:54,533
and entrust it to an evil ghost
like Jang Man-wol?

74
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:57,447
Strictly speaking,
she is not an evil ghost.

75
00:08:58,163 --> 00:08:59,213
Also,

76
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:02,289
she will also go to the other world soon.

77
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,535
So I was told.

78
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,920
I heard the one who will guide her
to the other world

79
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:07,674
has been sent there.

80
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,393
They want to send

81
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:15,757
Man-wol to the other world that easily?

82
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:20,725
Her soul can't go
to the other world so easily.

83
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:23,734
Her ill-fated relationship
of this life will be repeated.

84
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:29,146
She will hurt humans again,

85
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:32,818
and she will be sent to the afterlife
as an evil ghost.

86
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:41,210
I'm glad you're leaving here
after a good rest.

87
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:47,002
If you found your wife who died with you,

88
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:49,087
you could have departed together.

89
00:09:49,339 --> 00:09:52,339
I hope you will reunite with her
in the afterlife.

90
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:55,965
The platform for the afterlife is
that way. I'll take you there.

91
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,560
Honey?

92
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:06,613
Honey.

93
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,820
What are you doing here?

94
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,320
I'm here because I'm dead.

95
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:13,403
Do you know how much I looked for you
as soon as I died?

96
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,371
You're dead too?

97
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:17,448
I thought you were saved.

98
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:20,160
Who is this guy?

99
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:23,408
Are you having an affair
with that little brat as soon as you died?

100
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:24,618
Be careful what you say!

101
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:27,251
He died young.
He's actually three years older than you!

102
00:10:28,086 --> 00:10:29,166
Sweetheart.

103
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:31,758
-"Sweetheart"?
-What?

104
00:10:32,382 --> 00:10:33,552
Who are you?

105
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:35,591
Who are you?

106
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,011
Don't you dare touch him!

107
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:39,596
He is my first love!

108
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:41,984
Are you crazy?

109
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:43,475
You can't do this here, sir.

110
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,560
Yes, I'm crazy.

111
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,354
Don't you dare touch him,
and just go your way.

112
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,607
I'm going to kill you!

113
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:50,528
She's already dead.

114
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:51,778
You don't need to kill her.

115
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:54,856
Let me go. I will kill her!

116
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:00,742
Mr. Koo!

117
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:01,947
I'll kill you.

118
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:04,499
-Are you all right?
-I'm fine.

119
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:06,501
Just leave him be.

120
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:25,023
This hotel provides all the services

121
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:26,521
our guests desire.

122
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,560
You are already dead.

123
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:31,766
It is not difficult for you to die again.

124
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:34,651
Kill her as much as you want
until you feel better.

125
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,400
Now...

126
00:11:37,322 --> 00:11:38,912
What do you want to kill her with?

127
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:40,697
Pick one.

128
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:45,750
Sir, slash and chop her with this.

129
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,625
Ma'am, you can't just stand still.

130
00:11:48,917 --> 00:11:49,997
Chop him properly.

131
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,048
This way please.

132
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:56,128
Now, there will be a lot of blood
and flesh everywhere.

133
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:57,634
Everyone take a step back.

134
00:11:59,302 --> 00:12:00,802
You are all dead.

135
00:12:00,887 --> 00:12:04,217
But you can inflict deadly pain
on the other person's soul.

136
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:09,398
Please hack up the time you lived
together to your heart's content.

137
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:12,319
Slash it, tear it,

138
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:13,478
and destroy it.

139
00:12:13,983 --> 00:12:17,703
We will do our best to help you
vent out your grudges.

140
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:20,534
What are you doing? When a couple fights,

141
00:12:20,615 --> 00:12:22,905
you should try to stop them
and persuade them to live happily.

142
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,492
What do you think you're doing?

143
00:12:25,954 --> 00:12:27,874
How can you live happily?

144
00:12:27,956 --> 00:12:29,416
You are already dead.

145
00:12:30,792 --> 00:12:33,802
You don't even have one second to live.

146
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:35,213
Just vent out your grudges.

147
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:38,128
Whether you hack each other,
or bathe in blood,

148
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:41,006
enjoy to your hearts' content. Bye.

149
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:50,230
-That's enough.
-Stop fighting.

150
00:12:52,230 --> 00:12:53,520
Stop now.

151
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,573
You shouldn't fight.

152
00:12:56,818 --> 00:12:58,188
That's good.

153
00:13:10,999 --> 00:13:14,289
They were lovebirds
when they were alive. Such a pity.

154
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:17,419
Her first love, who she truly loved, died.

155
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:20,965
She married some random guy
out of despair.

156
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:24,140
An untimely encounter took place
in front of the door to the afterlife.

157
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:26,719
Remember the last time
when the guests who had debt problems

158
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:28,306
met here and caused a great commotion?

159
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:32,351
They have no need for money after death.
But they fought like cats and dogs.

160
00:13:32,437 --> 00:13:34,687
Whether it's big or small,
they had their grudges.

161
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:36,732
Fighting can be a way
of resolving grudges.

162
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:42,412
Here is <i>patbingsu</i>.

163
00:13:42,739 --> 00:13:45,739
I'll be going to resolve
the wife's grudges.

164
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:49,035
She wants to have the <i>patbingsu</i>
that she had with her first love

165
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,870
on their first date.

166
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:04,336
What is it?

167
00:14:04,886 --> 00:14:08,306
They're soju and roasted seaweed
you enjoyed when you were alive.

168
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:11,269
I heard from your wife
that she always prepared them for you.

169
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:14,150
She's so mean.

170
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:20,033
It's a mean question to ask
in this situation,

171
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:23,359
but don't you have anyone else
in your heart?

172
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:27,738
I don't.
For me, my wife was my first love.

173
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:30,369
It feels so unfair that I'm going to die.

174
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:36,789
You are already dead.

175
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:41,592
I'm glad the guests have calmed down.

176
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:44,972
You were hit, weren't you?
You have to be careful of angry ghosts.

177
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,386
It didn't hurt that much.

178
00:14:46,469 --> 00:14:49,599
That's not important.
You were hit by an evil grudge.

179
00:14:49,764 --> 00:14:52,894
-An evil grudge?
-The grudge of that guest

180
00:14:54,102 --> 00:14:55,482
has hit you.

181
00:14:57,522 --> 00:14:58,862
It could have been dangerous.

182
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:03,073
But Ms. Jang was watching it,
so you'll be fine.

183
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:05,151
Ms. Jang?

184
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:21,299
She probably came because it was too loud.

185
00:15:21,379 --> 00:15:24,589
Whether our guests fight
or have a bloody battle,

186
00:15:24,674 --> 00:15:26,844
she hardly ever cares about it.

187
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:28,553
But she stepped up today.

188
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:31,306
I think she did that because she was
worried you'd be hit again.

189
00:15:31,848 --> 00:15:32,848
Well...

190
00:15:33,349 --> 00:15:36,639
I don't usually get beaten up by others.

191
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,770
Since you were hit by a ghost,

192
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:42,066
you should sprinkle some salt
to ward off evil influence.

193
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:43,030
Like this.

194
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:50,316
She told me she would protect me.

195
00:15:51,242 --> 00:15:52,912
She really did protect me.

196
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:55,116
But it's a little...

197
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:58,253
embarrassing.

198
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:16,888
It's the sea.

199
00:16:20,188 --> 00:16:21,768
<i>The sea looks really beautiful.</i>

200
00:16:23,483 --> 00:16:26,073
I'm a little sad.

201
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:29,105
Because the sea

202
00:16:29,572 --> 00:16:31,572
looks more beautiful now...

203
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,036
than it did earlier.

204
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:03,693
Jang Man-wol.

205
00:17:04,357 --> 00:17:05,817
I came to check something.

206
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,780
If you're going to nag, do it later.

207
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:10,112
I'm doing my nails now,
and it's going great.

208
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:12,783
If these get ruined, I'll kill you.

209
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:14,869
Goodness.

210
00:17:14,951 --> 00:17:17,951
I can't believe you got beaten up
by a ghost like a loser.

211
00:17:20,540 --> 00:17:22,920
That's the color of the blue sea.

212
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,460
Yes, they're pretty, aren't they?

213
00:17:25,545 --> 00:17:27,955
They are. Very sadly.

214
00:17:32,093 --> 00:17:34,143
The reason you were sad on the beach...

215
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:37,852
was this?

216
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,392
Because there was no yacht?

217
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:41,475
Goodness, it got here?

218
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:44,732
It was sent from Norway,
so I thought it would take a while.

219
00:17:44,814 --> 00:17:46,824
But it got here quickly. Give it to me.

220
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:49,145
Are you going to buy that?

221
00:17:49,694 --> 00:17:52,534
I sold all of my cars.
I could use a yacht.

222
00:17:52,655 --> 00:17:54,655
You don't have any place to go
on that yacht.

223
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,240
Of course, I have places to go.

224
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:57,735
What's that thing called?

225
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,000
Right, <i>The Fishermen and the City</i>.

226
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:03,079
They go around the country on a boat
catching fish.

227
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:06,381
Don't worry.
I have many places to go on a yacht.

228
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:08,550
What about the money? Can you afford it?

229
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,967
That's the problem.

230
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,847
That painting of the tiger.
Is no one willing to buy that?

231
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:17,850
Try to sell it for a quarter of the price.

232
00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:19,432
You can't get a yacht.

233
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:20,595
If you want to go fishing,

234
00:18:20,683 --> 00:18:22,563
I'll take you
to a fishing hole in Wolmi Island.

235
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:23,813
We can get there by car.

236
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:25,194
You sold all of my cars.

237
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:26,441
We have two left.

238
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,482
What? You said I still have three.

239
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,935
Right, three of them. I got confused.

240
00:18:32,028 --> 00:18:33,648
Gosh, you scared me.

241
00:18:34,572 --> 00:18:35,532
I'm so relieved.

242
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:37,065
That's a relief, right?

243
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:40,160
Then let's drive to Wolmi Island.
I'll find a great restaurant too.

244
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:41,911
I will

245
00:18:42,747 --> 00:18:44,457
cancel this request myself.

246
00:18:52,715 --> 00:18:55,175
Everything got ruined
in the perfect timing.

247
00:18:57,762 --> 00:19:00,892
The color blue and Wolmi Island
don't really go well together.

248
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:05,188
Wolmi Island is famous for the ride,
Ghost Pang Pang.

249
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:08,808
I'll switch to a color
that stands out a bit more.

250
00:19:09,315 --> 00:19:11,935
<i>Wolmi Island</i>

251
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:30,205
TO MS. JANG MAN-WOL, I LOVE YOU

252
00:19:34,465 --> 00:19:37,795
He told me to sprinkle salt,
so seasoned salt should be fine, right?

253
00:19:49,397 --> 00:19:50,647
Chan-sung, what are you doing?

254
00:19:51,524 --> 00:19:52,404
Hey.

255
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:55,491
You didn't go to work yet?

256
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:57,409
I'm about to leave. What's that?

257
00:19:57,488 --> 00:19:59,318
Oh, salt.

258
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:01,827
What are you doing with that?
Did something awful happen?

259
00:20:01,909 --> 00:20:04,539
I heard it's great to sprinkle salt
to prevent evil influence.

260
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:07,540
"Evil influence"?
You aren't talking about Mi-ra, are you?

261
00:20:08,124 --> 00:20:11,174
Did Mi-ra steal your credit card again?

262
00:20:11,252 --> 00:20:13,672
Did she borrow money under your name?

263
00:20:13,963 --> 00:20:16,093
Yes, Mi-ra did that to me long ago.

264
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:18,627
I just remembered how angry I was.

265
00:20:18,718 --> 00:20:19,888
Hey, forget the seasoned salt.

266
00:20:19,969 --> 00:20:21,799
There's Himalayan pink salt.
Do you want it?

267
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:23,967
I don't need to use
such good salt for this.

268
00:20:24,265 --> 00:20:25,635
Seasoned salt should be enough.

269
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:28,352
Give it to me.
I'll cover every single inch.

270
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,228
Okay.

271
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:37,402
Hey, Sanchez.
You're seasoning me a bit too much.

272
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:38,896
You aren't making kimchi right now.

273
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,030
It's stuck. It won't come out.

274
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:43,528
Really?

275
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:46,754
Will Man-wol buy the yacht?

276
00:20:49,582 --> 00:20:51,882
You set her up
with the yacht company in Norway?

277
00:20:51,959 --> 00:20:54,339
I uploaded a picture of my yacht
on my social media.

278
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:57,010
She saw that and asked me
where I got it, so I told her.

279
00:20:57,089 --> 00:20:59,679
She was going to get
something that expensive?

280
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:01,259
She's the owner of your hotel.

281
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:02,603
She can afford that much.

282
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:05,678
I was going to let her join
our yacht club too.

283
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:08,393
Your yacht club?
The wealthy people's social club?

284
00:21:08,476 --> 00:21:10,806
It's going to help her
with her business too.

285
00:21:10,895 --> 00:21:12,475
She's not dating anyone, is she?

286
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:15,071
Why do you ask?

287
00:21:15,149 --> 00:21:16,729
I want to set her up
with one of our members.

288
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,817
If it's a yacht club,
you should go ride on a yacht.

289
00:21:18,903 --> 00:21:20,283
Why are you setting people up?

290
00:21:20,362 --> 00:21:22,912
People meet partners for their businesses

291
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:24,700
and their lives in such clubs.

292
00:21:24,784 --> 00:21:26,414
That's where I met Veronica.

293
00:21:26,994 --> 00:21:28,204
What do you think about him?

294
00:21:28,496 --> 00:21:30,036
Don't you think he's a good match for her?

295
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:33,831
He's way too thin.

296
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:35,246
He is?

297
00:21:35,336 --> 00:21:36,666
Jang Man-wol likes

298
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:40,554
someone like Kim Jun-hyun.
A type like Kim Jun-hyun.

299
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:42,723
People who can eat five dumplings
in one bite.

300
00:21:42,802 --> 00:21:45,512
Really? In that case,
what about him? He's okay, right?

301
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:50,943
He looks way too young.

302
00:21:51,018 --> 00:21:52,138
He's well over 30.

303
00:21:52,228 --> 00:21:55,358
Jang Man-wol is older than you think.

304
00:21:55,439 --> 00:21:57,899
No matter what you expect,
she's older than that.

305
00:21:57,983 --> 00:21:59,113
He's way too young.

306
00:21:59,193 --> 00:22:01,493
In that case, who could be the best?

307
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:04,660
Sanchez, she has no money to buy a yacht.

308
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:06,740
She doesn't qualify
to be a part of the club.

309
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:09,946
So don't set her up with any of them.
Don't do it.

310
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:12,747
In that case, she can join
our tennis club or golf club

311
00:22:12,832 --> 00:22:15,382
-instead of the yacht club, or--
-Sanchez.

312
00:22:19,046 --> 00:22:22,256
Since when were you into sports?

313
00:22:22,925 --> 00:22:24,335
You're such a sportsman.

314
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:30,390
But she isn't interested in sports.
Leave her alone.

315
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:38,113
Where's the Himalayan pink salt?

316
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:39,360
Over there.

317
00:22:41,277 --> 00:22:43,067
He must like her.

318
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,873
Goodness, he made a mess here.

319
00:22:47,575 --> 00:22:50,195
Gosh, this is sweet. Hey, this is sugar.

320
00:22:50,828 --> 00:22:52,288
Did you sprinkle sugar on yourself?

321
00:22:52,371 --> 00:22:54,831
Man, you'll get cockroaches in here.

322
00:23:18,981 --> 00:23:21,731
This is the punishment
for corrupting the order of this world.

323
00:23:21,817 --> 00:23:23,317
You must vanish immediately.

324
00:23:38,584 --> 00:23:40,254
She has grown really weak.

325
00:23:40,544 --> 00:23:42,594
I'm going to take over her body.

326
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:44,835
Hey. Hey!

327
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:56,305
No! Stop!

328
00:23:56,602 --> 00:23:57,652
No!

329
00:24:01,398 --> 00:24:02,398
Hey.

330
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:04,435
Come here.

331
00:24:06,236 --> 00:24:07,486
Is she okay?

332
00:24:08,530 --> 00:24:10,660
-Did she go insane?
-Did she go crazy?

333
00:24:10,741 --> 00:24:11,701
What are we going to do?

334
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:13,084
Should we call the teacher?

335
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:14,620
Hey, we should call 911.

336
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:16,583
Hey, report this.

337
00:24:16,664 --> 00:24:18,044
Should we talk to her?

338
00:24:18,749 --> 00:24:20,079
Maybe she really sees ghosts.

339
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:22,837
-Can you please step aside?
-Oh, no.

340
00:24:33,514 --> 00:24:34,724
Stop it.

341
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:37,353
No. No way.

342
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:40,483
Yu-na, it's me.

343
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:48,360
You can come out now.

344
00:25:15,472 --> 00:25:16,522
It's okay.

345
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:18,429
Let's go.

346
00:25:27,276 --> 00:25:29,236
Is there a place
where she can lie down and rest?

347
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:31,281
The infirmary is
at the end of the hallway.

348
00:25:31,447 --> 00:25:32,447
Thanks.

349
00:26:04,188 --> 00:26:06,018
Something must've happened to her.

350
00:26:15,365 --> 00:26:19,195
It was the fourth Mago
that hurt my intern, wasn't it?

351
00:26:19,411 --> 00:26:20,911
The number four in the black dress.

352
00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:22,956
Don't dare to number the deities.

353
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:26,420
Though they look different,
they're one with greater plans.

354
00:26:26,502 --> 00:26:29,552
Don't you think it's lame to say
that they have greater plans

355
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:33,220
when they don't even appear
in the way humans want them to?

356
00:26:33,759 --> 00:26:35,589
Mago wanted

357
00:26:35,761 --> 00:26:38,141
the vengeful ghost that stayed
at the hotel as a guest.

358
00:26:38,222 --> 00:26:40,772
If Mago finds it, will she get rid of it?

359
00:26:40,849 --> 00:26:43,559
Another Mago wants
to bring it back to the hotel.

360
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:48,016
The greater plans of the deities are
always so darn confusing.

361
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:52,606
They can be generous and cruel.
That's how the deities are.

362
00:26:54,404 --> 00:26:57,664
The first one wants me
to go to the afterlife,

363
00:26:57,783 --> 00:27:01,123
and the fourth one wants to destroy me
once I become an evil ghost.

364
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:03,870
You're right, they're all deities.

365
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:06,751
But who do you think is stronger?

366
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:09,174
The first one, or the fourth one?

367
00:27:09,253 --> 00:27:10,303
Don't you dare...

368
00:27:11,255 --> 00:27:12,835
to number the deities.

369
00:27:14,174 --> 00:27:16,054
You're just avoiding to answer that.

370
00:27:16,635 --> 00:27:19,385
Whoever is stronger,
they only have one goal.

371
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:23,725
Anyway, I will have to leave here.

372
00:27:32,526 --> 00:27:34,816
-What's that?
-This is my answer.

373
00:27:45,789 --> 00:27:48,629
Yu-na felt something odd
from the cellphone.

374
00:27:48,709 --> 00:27:51,339
I think the guest of Room 13
harmed a human

375
00:27:51,420 --> 00:27:54,760
by spreading a video through the network.

376
00:27:57,718 --> 00:28:00,888
We'll only know
when we open the video link.

377
00:28:00,971 --> 00:28:02,431
But to make the ghost appear,

378
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:04,934
we'll need to use a human as bait.

379
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:06,765
Who should open the link?

380
00:28:06,852 --> 00:28:09,902
No one comes to my mind.

381
00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:13,646
There's only one human at this hotel
who can be the bait.

382
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:16,570
Get Chan-sung.

383
00:28:24,077 --> 00:28:25,117
No.

384
00:28:27,748 --> 00:28:29,578
Based on what's being said
in the group chat,

385
00:28:29,666 --> 00:28:31,706
I'm sure it's a sex tape
filmed without consent.

386
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:33,593
Filming such a thing
is a criminal offense,

387
00:28:33,670 --> 00:28:35,170
so is watching it.

388
00:28:35,255 --> 00:28:37,005
I'll never watch anything like this, ever.

389
00:28:47,517 --> 00:28:50,307
What a great man.
What a smart man you are.

390
00:28:52,648 --> 00:28:56,028
But you have to be brave.
We have to find a ghost.

391
00:28:57,277 --> 00:28:58,107
With this?

392
00:28:58,195 --> 00:29:00,775
It's the guest that stayed in Room 13.

393
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:03,454
We have to open it to find the ghost.

394
00:29:03,533 --> 00:29:05,583
You're saying
that the guest became vengeful

395
00:29:05,661 --> 00:29:08,251
because of some accident
involving this video?

396
00:29:08,330 --> 00:29:12,710
The video might be unpleasant,
or it might be terrifying.

397
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:14,460
Are you up for it?

398
00:29:33,355 --> 00:29:35,265
IT'S THE FAMOUS VIDEO? I DIDN'T WATCH IT.

399
00:29:45,409 --> 00:29:46,409
I see an empty room.

400
00:29:47,536 --> 00:29:48,576
There's no one.

401
00:29:52,457 --> 00:29:56,377
Yu-na said that she felt something
when the phone rang.

402
00:29:56,628 --> 00:29:58,048
<i>This is where the ghost was.</i>

403
00:30:03,427 --> 00:30:04,297
Here.

404
00:30:08,473 --> 00:30:12,483
<i>I can still feel the grudge of her here.</i>

405
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:14,595
<i>She created this room.</i>

406
00:30:15,105 --> 00:30:17,515
So you're saying this wasn't
an illegally filmed video?

407
00:30:17,941 --> 00:30:18,941
<i>No,</i>

408
00:30:19,443 --> 00:30:23,243
<i>this is just a room that's built
with the grudge of a ghost.</i>

409
00:30:24,448 --> 00:30:26,068
<i>There must be a few more like this.</i>

410
00:30:26,158 --> 00:30:29,868
Yu-na said that she felt something eerie
even before the man played the video.

411
00:30:29,953 --> 00:30:32,413
She sent the video only to her targets.

412
00:30:32,497 --> 00:30:35,377
Then there must be a next one.

413
00:30:36,418 --> 00:30:37,748
Where could she be right now?

414
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:39,126
<i>She's probably sent a video</i>

415
00:30:39,212 --> 00:30:41,342
<i>of a room that looks just like this
to the next target,</i>

416
00:30:41,757 --> 00:30:45,007
<i>ready to kill him when he plays the video.</i>

417
00:31:00,108 --> 00:31:02,108
Get off the phone when you're with her.

418
00:31:02,194 --> 00:31:05,074
It's for work. I have to send
something to a client.

419
00:31:51,201 --> 00:31:52,291
Honey.

420
00:31:53,787 --> 00:31:55,207
Honey!

421
00:32:01,711 --> 00:32:04,761
It has been five years
since my sister died,

422
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:08,142
but the video is still found online.

423
00:32:09,136 --> 00:32:11,846
You must be quite familiar
with cases like this.

424
00:32:12,556 --> 00:32:14,516
There's no way we can get
the videos off the Internet.

425
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:16,564
That's true.

426
00:32:17,185 --> 00:32:19,185
Were those who distributed
the video punished?

427
00:32:20,230 --> 00:32:21,520
Punished?

428
00:32:22,524 --> 00:32:25,444
All they had to do was pay
some fines when Ga-yeong died.

429
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,040
Is this man related to the incident?

430
00:32:34,536 --> 00:32:36,196
He and Ga-yeong went to the same college.

431
00:32:36,621 --> 00:32:39,881
The video was shared
in the group chat for male students.

432
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:41,378
That's where the video was leaked.

433
00:32:51,136 --> 00:32:53,556
<i>Her classmates laughed at her</i>

434
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:56,218
<i>watching the video together.</i>

435
00:33:00,604 --> 00:33:03,024
-Look at that.
-Amazing.

436
00:33:04,441 --> 00:33:07,441
Do you remember who watched the video?

437
00:33:07,527 --> 00:33:08,697
How can I forget?

438
00:33:08,778 --> 00:33:10,408
I still remember all their names.

439
00:33:10,947 --> 00:33:13,487
Had just one of them told us
about the video,

440
00:33:13,575 --> 00:33:15,365
we would've prevented it from spreading.

441
00:33:15,577 --> 00:33:16,947
Then maybe my sister...

442
00:33:19,956 --> 00:33:21,206
wouldn't have died.

443
00:33:23,126 --> 00:33:25,166
<i>My sister locked herself in her room
like a lunatic</i>

444
00:33:25,378 --> 00:33:28,418
<i>and looked all over online to see
if there were more videos of herself.</i>

445
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:31,184
<i>She was slowly dying.</i>

446
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:32,639
THE QUEEN OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERING

447
00:33:46,942 --> 00:33:48,152
Now that she's dead,

448
00:33:48,485 --> 00:33:50,775
she must be in peace
free from pain. Right?

449
00:33:56,243 --> 00:33:57,623
I truly...

450
00:33:58,745 --> 00:34:00,075
hope so as well.

451
00:34:24,104 --> 00:34:25,984
The man who filmed the video and sold it

452
00:34:26,064 --> 00:34:27,984
was also a member of the group chat.

453
00:34:33,947 --> 00:34:35,157
<i>What's funny is</i>

454
00:34:35,282 --> 00:34:37,582
<i>that the man now owns
a video-sharing platform,</i>

455
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:39,699
<i>getting rich and having a nice life.</i>

456
00:34:50,964 --> 00:34:54,684
He really is living a nice life.
So nice that I want to kill him.

457
00:34:54,801 --> 00:34:57,641
Don't get so mad. It'll drain your energy.

458
00:34:58,013 --> 00:34:59,813
This is delicious. Try it.

459
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:04,059
No, thanks.

460
00:35:04,603 --> 00:35:07,693
The last one is always the best one.

461
00:35:08,607 --> 00:35:12,067
See? The vengeful ghost left
the best one for the last too.

462
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:14,235
That's why I'm sure she'll come for him.

463
00:35:14,321 --> 00:35:16,411
All we need to do is just to take
his phone to our hotel

464
00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:18,239
before the video is sent to it.

465
00:35:19,576 --> 00:35:20,446
Really?

466
00:35:20,535 --> 00:35:23,285
Do you think she will really leave
the last target here and follow us?

467
00:35:26,916 --> 00:35:28,836
I can't believe somebody like him is
so well off.

468
00:35:29,711 --> 00:35:31,171
The deities are so unfair.

469
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:33,338
That's why I don't like them.

470
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:40,060
As I said, the last one is
always the best one.

471
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:51,517
{\an8}You're Mr. Koo Chan-sung,
the manager of Hotel del Luna?

472
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:53,574
Del Luna.

473
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:57,203
It must be new.

474
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:59,910
No, it's been around for a very long time.

475
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:03,662
Are you here to post
an advertisement on our website?

476
00:36:03,745 --> 00:36:04,745
No.

477
00:36:05,622 --> 00:36:07,672
We're here on behalf of our guest.

478
00:36:07,749 --> 00:36:09,209
She desperately wishes

479
00:36:10,377 --> 00:36:12,047
to meet you.

480
00:36:12,128 --> 00:36:13,208
Me?

481
00:36:14,839 --> 00:36:17,469
Who is she? Why does she want to meet me?

482
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:19,014
She's someone

483
00:36:20,178 --> 00:36:22,428
who holds a lot of grudges against you.

484
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:23,969
Against me?

485
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:28,977
I've never done anything for anyone
to feel that way against me.

486
00:36:33,733 --> 00:36:34,903
What are you doing?

487
00:36:36,152 --> 00:36:38,452
You have a really nice yacht.

488
00:36:39,155 --> 00:36:40,945
I'm also planning to buy one like yours.

489
00:36:41,825 --> 00:36:43,275
She's the hotel owner.

490
00:36:44,577 --> 00:36:49,247
My gosh, you've traveled
to so many incredible places.

491
00:36:49,332 --> 00:36:51,632
I should go to these places before I die.

492
00:36:53,837 --> 00:36:55,127
That's enough.

493
00:36:55,714 --> 00:36:58,554
It's rude to take photos
of someone's private space

494
00:36:58,758 --> 00:36:59,838
without their permission.

495
00:37:00,885 --> 00:37:01,925
Really?

496
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:08,728
What was that?

497
00:37:10,145 --> 00:37:12,305
You have a wedgie.

498
00:37:13,189 --> 00:37:14,109
Hey.

499
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:16,110
How much do I get paid if I upload

500
00:37:16,192 --> 00:37:19,572
an illicit photo like this
on your website?

501
00:37:20,321 --> 00:37:22,451
One hundred won? Two hundred?

502
00:37:22,782 --> 00:37:26,162
I wonder how many of these photos
need to get uploaded

503
00:37:26,494 --> 00:37:29,584
for you to be able to buy a yacht
and travel to all those places?

504
00:37:31,124 --> 00:37:33,794
-About a million?
-Are you digging into something?

505
00:37:34,419 --> 00:37:36,669
Are you guys reporters? Or cops?

506
00:37:37,589 --> 00:37:39,669
The hotel was just a lie, wasn't it?

507
00:37:40,300 --> 00:37:43,390
No wonder I had never heard of it.

508
00:37:43,470 --> 00:37:45,720
I guess we should invite you over one day

509
00:37:45,805 --> 00:37:47,675
in order to show you that it wasn't a lie.

510
00:37:49,434 --> 00:37:51,354
Get out of here right now

511
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:53,441
before I call the guards.

512
00:38:00,487 --> 00:38:01,817
Whenever

513
00:38:02,405 --> 00:38:04,195
you see our hotel,

514
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:07,990
please feel free to visit.

515
00:38:10,663 --> 00:38:11,583
Let's go.

516
00:38:15,502 --> 00:38:17,922
"Always do your best.

517
00:38:18,213 --> 00:38:20,553
The deities will take care of the rest."

518
00:38:23,676 --> 00:38:26,096
Seriously? You believe this kind of stuff?

519
00:38:26,971 --> 00:38:30,681
I'm a very religious man.

520
00:38:32,519 --> 00:38:37,109
If the deities gave you this kind
of life even after what you did,

521
00:38:39,692 --> 00:38:41,742
it just shows how unreasonable
the deities are.

522
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:02,050
It's his cell phone.

523
00:39:05,718 --> 00:39:07,388
Good job, Chan-sung.

524
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:09,890
We need to get to the hotel
before the video is sent to the phone.

525
00:39:09,973 --> 00:39:11,063
We should hurry.

526
00:39:16,938 --> 00:39:19,818
Chan-sung did his best
regardless of how weak he is.

527
00:39:21,526 --> 00:39:23,316
I wonder if the deities would do the same.

528
00:39:35,915 --> 00:39:38,745
It's been quite long.
Why isn't the video link here yet?

529
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:40,800
Is the cell phone out of battery?

530
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,920
The Wi-Fi here works just fine.

531
00:39:43,673 --> 00:39:46,513
The others definitely got the video
through their cell phones.

532
00:39:48,761 --> 00:39:49,891
Cell phones are...

533
00:39:51,139 --> 00:39:53,269
not the only routes to send the video.

534
00:39:58,646 --> 00:40:00,516
Did you check the CCTV footages?

535
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:05,776
Those people who came in the afternoon
definitely stole my cell phone.

536
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:09,487
The CCTV footage during that time
all got deleted for some reason.

537
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:11,869
Are you kidding me?

538
00:40:13,703 --> 00:40:15,713
We have so many CCTVs.

539
00:40:16,372 --> 00:40:17,832
You better find it no matter what.

540
00:40:18,207 --> 00:40:19,207
Yes, sir.

541
00:40:44,609 --> 00:40:47,069
I guess she can send the video
through other routes.

542
00:40:47,946 --> 00:40:48,986
I should go back there.

543
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:51,450
Chan-sung, your job is done here.

544
00:40:53,576 --> 00:40:54,946
The rest will be taken care of.

545
00:40:56,663 --> 00:40:58,713
What do you mean? By whom?

546
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:01,788
Mago will show up there.

547
00:41:05,004 --> 00:41:07,514
I'm curious to know
what form she'll appear in.

548
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,876
I wonder if she'll be merciful

549
00:41:10,718 --> 00:41:12,048
or cruel.

550
00:41:19,519 --> 00:41:21,099
CEO, JEONG EUN-SEOK

551
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:35,485
HERE'S THE VIDEO YOU'VE BEEN WAITING FOR

552
00:41:45,837 --> 00:41:46,837
What's this?

553
00:41:47,547 --> 00:41:49,217
It's not the CCTV footage of my office.

554
00:41:50,591 --> 00:41:51,681
What is this?

555
00:42:06,441 --> 00:42:07,691
My gosh, what is this?

556
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:21,498
What?

557
00:42:27,003 --> 00:42:28,053
Was it hacked?

558
00:42:29,714 --> 00:42:31,974
The security system must be a mess.

559
00:43:12,298 --> 00:43:13,378
Look at me.

560
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:23,730
Who are you?

561
00:43:26,896 --> 00:43:28,476
I'll kill you.

562
00:45:30,561 --> 00:45:33,941
You're an evil ghost
that has harmed humans.

563
00:45:38,819 --> 00:45:40,489
You shall vanish here and now.

564
00:46:20,903 --> 00:46:22,323
<i>Now that she's dead,</i>

565
00:46:22,738 --> 00:46:25,738
<i>she must be in peace
free from pain. Right?</i>

566
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:06,722
<i>Why won't the deities appear in the way
humans want them to?</i>

567
00:48:13,390 --> 00:48:16,940
This is a glass of a cocktail
to console the soul who has gone.

568
00:48:17,853 --> 00:48:20,153
I think Mr. Koo is heartbroken.

569
00:48:20,231 --> 00:48:23,481
He had his chin up high
after sending off a few customers,

570
00:48:23,567 --> 00:48:25,147
but this incident gave him a burn.

571
00:48:28,364 --> 00:48:29,954
Gosh, that's hot!

572
00:48:34,954 --> 00:48:35,964
It's hot.

573
00:48:36,330 --> 00:48:38,540
He's hurt because he was sincere.

574
00:48:38,624 --> 00:48:40,794
Mr. Koo is a good man.

575
00:48:41,836 --> 00:48:43,496
It's so hard to hate him.

576
00:48:56,308 --> 00:48:59,188
Nothing would have changed
even if you had arrived there earlier.

577
00:48:59,812 --> 00:49:02,022
It's what the deities decided.

578
00:49:06,068 --> 00:49:07,568
Could the same happen

579
00:49:08,863 --> 00:49:10,663
to all of you here too?

580
00:49:11,866 --> 00:49:13,026
Do you mean vanishing?

581
00:49:14,451 --> 00:49:15,491
Yes.

582
00:49:16,829 --> 00:49:18,829
We're all souls after all.

583
00:49:20,124 --> 00:49:23,504
If we stay behind in this world
instead of going to the afterlife,

584
00:49:24,128 --> 00:49:26,128
there's always a chance
the same could happen to us.

585
00:49:28,215 --> 00:49:29,425
If it's dangerous,

586
00:49:30,593 --> 00:49:32,013
why are you still here?

587
00:49:32,636 --> 00:49:35,506
Did you have a sad and painful death
just like her?

588
00:49:36,390 --> 00:49:38,890
Is it the same for all of you?

589
00:49:38,976 --> 00:49:42,056
Mr. Kim and Ms. Choe too?

590
00:49:52,323 --> 00:49:53,743
But

591
00:49:53,824 --> 00:49:57,244
we won't run out there and make trouble.

592
00:49:58,412 --> 00:49:59,752
Don't worry.

593
00:50:20,434 --> 00:50:25,274
{\an8}YOU'RE INVITED TO HOTEL DEL LUNA

594
00:50:29,401 --> 00:50:33,071
{\an8}PRESIDENT JANG MAN-WOL

595
00:50:45,626 --> 00:50:46,786
Go mail this out.

596
00:50:50,422 --> 00:50:51,422
What is this?

597
00:50:51,924 --> 00:50:52,974
An invitation.

598
00:50:54,260 --> 00:50:55,930
We promised to invite him, remember?

599
00:50:56,804 --> 00:50:58,264
Are you going to invite him?

600
00:50:58,639 --> 00:51:00,349
But our guest is already gone.

601
00:51:00,516 --> 00:51:03,136
We failed to serve
one of our guests properly.

602
00:51:03,602 --> 00:51:07,902
That's why we should do
what she wanted to do in her stead.

603
00:51:09,316 --> 00:51:10,896
We'll do the best we can.

604
00:51:33,841 --> 00:51:36,261
{\an8}TO MR. JEONG EUN-SEOK

605
00:51:37,428 --> 00:51:38,798
"Hotel del Luna"?

606
00:51:39,972 --> 00:51:43,142
Whenever you see our hotel,

607
00:51:44,143 --> 00:51:46,983
please feel free to visit.

608
00:51:49,690 --> 00:51:50,860
This is eerie.

609
00:52:53,045 --> 00:52:55,005
YOUR DESTINATION HAS CHANGED

610
00:52:56,757 --> 00:52:57,967
<i>Turn left.</i>

611
00:53:04,223 --> 00:53:05,563
<i>Turn right.</i>

612
00:53:10,604 --> 00:53:11,694
<i>Go straight.</i>

613
00:53:14,525 --> 00:53:15,525
<i>Turn left.</i>

614
00:53:16,276 --> 00:53:17,276
<i>Turn right.</i>

615
00:53:19,571 --> 00:53:20,701
<i>Make a U-turn.</i>

616
00:53:23,951 --> 00:53:25,951
229-7, MYEONG-DONG 8-GIL

617
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:31,537
<i>Straight.</i>

618
00:53:33,085 --> 00:53:34,085
Is it really this way?

619
00:53:34,169 --> 00:53:36,919
<i>I said, go straight. Straight.</i>

620
00:53:37,965 --> 00:53:38,965
<i>Stop!</i>

621
00:53:48,725 --> 00:53:49,685
What is this?

622
00:53:59,903 --> 00:54:01,243
What is this place?

623
00:54:02,823 --> 00:54:04,783
"Hotel del Luna"?

624
00:54:06,285 --> 00:54:07,655
Did I really come here?

625
00:54:30,517 --> 00:54:31,887
Welcome, sir.

626
00:54:32,186 --> 00:54:33,936
You received an invitation, didn't you?

627
00:54:35,314 --> 00:54:36,824
Ms. Jang is waiting for you.

628
00:54:37,316 --> 00:54:38,436
This way.

629
00:54:49,077 --> 00:54:49,997
What?

630
00:54:50,621 --> 00:54:51,501
It's you.

631
00:54:54,666 --> 00:54:58,246
Welcome. We prepared
a room for you, Mr. Jeong.

632
00:54:59,213 --> 00:55:01,763
So this hotel really exists.

633
00:55:02,841 --> 00:55:03,931
How did you do this?

634
00:55:05,594 --> 00:55:07,304
Did you hack into my car?

635
00:55:11,266 --> 00:55:13,726
You came here with our owner's invitation.

636
00:55:18,065 --> 00:55:19,185
Please follow me.

637
00:55:40,462 --> 00:55:43,222
This is the room.
Like I told you last time,

638
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:45,925
the guest who looked for you
used to stay in this room.

639
00:55:52,766 --> 00:55:55,936
You said no one has a grudge against you.
Did someone come to your mind?

640
00:55:58,230 --> 00:56:00,900
I'll go in and find out
why you're doing this to me.

641
00:56:21,128 --> 00:56:22,168
This is...

642
00:56:29,303 --> 00:56:30,803
Do you know where this is?

643
00:56:33,015 --> 00:56:34,675
It's my old room.

644
00:56:34,766 --> 00:56:38,186
Do you also remember
the thing you did in this room?

645
00:57:28,987 --> 00:57:31,197
Why is this room here now?

646
00:57:31,740 --> 00:57:33,160
What is this place?

647
00:57:33,492 --> 00:57:37,042
A hotel right between this world
and the other world.

648
00:57:37,788 --> 00:57:39,578
A hotel for souls.

649
00:57:41,166 --> 00:57:42,826
Stop joking around.

650
00:57:43,126 --> 00:57:45,086
There's no such thing.

651
00:58:14,032 --> 00:58:15,242
Was that a dream?

652
00:58:15,325 --> 00:58:16,405
It wasn't.

653
00:58:18,745 --> 00:58:19,905
Who are you?

654
00:58:22,207 --> 00:58:23,957
I invited you to the hotel.

655
00:58:24,960 --> 00:58:26,550
So that wasn't a dream?

656
00:58:27,004 --> 00:58:29,214
It's not a place you can come in a dream.

657
00:58:29,673 --> 00:58:31,093
You can come only when you're dead.

658
00:58:31,174 --> 00:58:33,094
Wait, I'm dead?

659
00:58:34,386 --> 00:58:36,136
No, you aren't dead.

660
00:58:37,014 --> 00:58:38,974
I wanted to ask a question,

661
00:58:39,349 --> 00:58:41,059
so I had to bring your soul here.

662
00:58:41,143 --> 00:58:43,813
You're standing at the boundary
between life and death right now.

663
00:58:45,063 --> 00:58:46,113
What?

664
00:59:09,463 --> 00:59:11,513
Why are you in such a hurry?

665
00:59:11,631 --> 00:59:13,551
I told you that I had a question.

666
00:59:13,633 --> 00:59:15,513
What do you want to know?

667
00:59:16,928 --> 00:59:19,598
You've been to that room.
Do you remember now?

668
00:59:23,518 --> 00:59:25,728
Our guest who made a visit to you.

669
00:59:26,438 --> 00:59:28,068
Do you remember

670
00:59:29,024 --> 00:59:30,484
who that woman is?

671
00:59:33,028 --> 00:59:34,148
That woman...

672
00:59:34,738 --> 00:59:36,158
I will kill you.

673
00:59:42,621 --> 00:59:44,041
Who is that woman?

674
00:59:44,122 --> 00:59:45,332
You killed her.

675
00:59:45,749 --> 00:59:48,089
-I never killed anyone.
-You did.

676
00:59:48,710 --> 00:59:50,420
You stripped her naked
and kicked her outside,

677
00:59:50,504 --> 00:59:52,514
so she was stabbed to death
by everyone's eyes.

678
00:59:54,091 --> 00:59:55,221
You have to remember.

679
01:00:04,351 --> 01:00:07,561
I have no idea. I don't know who she is.

680
01:00:07,646 --> 01:00:09,606
It's what you did. Why don't you know?

681
01:00:09,689 --> 01:00:10,899
Try harder!

682
01:00:14,194 --> 01:00:16,744
Yes, it's something I did.

683
01:00:17,364 --> 01:00:20,284
But I have no idea who she is exactly.
There are so many!

684
01:00:55,193 --> 01:00:56,403
It was a dream.

685
01:00:57,237 --> 01:00:58,277
It was.

686
01:01:03,410 --> 01:01:05,450
Gosh, I thought I really died.

687
01:01:08,874 --> 01:01:12,384
<i>He didn't tell you a good answer.
Why did you send him back?</i>

688
01:01:15,463 --> 01:01:17,973
That's not what I was curious about.

689
01:01:20,051 --> 01:01:23,811
I tried my best to show
that he's the worst.

690
01:01:25,682 --> 01:01:27,482
Now, what will the deities do?

691
01:01:35,233 --> 01:01:37,863
I remember now. Yun Ga-yeong.

692
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:46,697
Right. I heard she committed suicide.

693
01:01:47,662 --> 01:01:49,412
I remember that now.

694
01:02:50,183 --> 01:02:53,233
<i>The victim of the train accident
at Gyeongbu Line this morning</i>

695
01:02:53,311 --> 01:02:57,071
<i>was identified as CEO Jeong Eun-seok
of World Disk, a file-sharing platform.</i>

696
01:02:57,274 --> 01:02:59,654
<i>Jeong was under investigation
by the police</i>

697
01:02:59,734 --> 01:03:02,954
<i>for distributing illegal pornography
and embezzling company funds.</i>

698
01:03:03,029 --> 01:03:06,069
{\an8}<i>The circumstances
of the accident are still unknown.</i>

699
01:03:06,157 --> 01:03:08,077
<i>The police have been investigating</i>

700
01:03:08,159 --> 01:03:11,039
<i>the gang members
for a connection with the porn videos,</i>

701
01:03:11,121 --> 01:03:12,961
<i>but the investigation has faced a dead end</i>

702
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:14,789
<i>since they couldn't find
any feasible connection.</i>

703
01:03:14,874 --> 01:03:17,544
{\an8}<i>The navigator and event data recorder
in Jeong's car...</i>

704
01:03:17,627 --> 01:03:20,957
I guess the deities really exist.

705
01:03:21,047 --> 01:03:22,507
<i>The investigation will not be easy.</i>

706
01:03:22,590 --> 01:03:25,510
<i>No other human lives were lost
in this accident.</i>

707
01:03:25,593 --> 01:03:28,313
<i>Those who got hurt on the train</i>

708
01:03:28,388 --> 01:03:32,268
<i>at the time of the accident are
being treated at a nearby hospital.</i>

709
01:03:36,938 --> 01:03:38,688
I'm feeling better now.

710
01:03:38,773 --> 01:03:40,783
I'm staying here
because I don't want to go to school.

711
01:03:40,859 --> 01:03:44,699
Tell your friends that it was
because of some bug and go back to school.

712
01:03:46,031 --> 01:03:49,331
If you like school that much,
you should come to my school.

713
01:03:49,868 --> 01:03:53,248
I mean, you can just show yourself
to people like you did the other day.

714
01:03:53,580 --> 01:03:55,210
I can't do that for long.

715
01:03:55,999 --> 01:03:57,169
Especially during the day.

716
01:03:58,710 --> 01:04:00,670
Then how about we get out of here now?

717
01:04:01,004 --> 01:04:02,344
I'll buy you something delicious.

718
01:04:03,590 --> 01:04:04,970
Where's my brother?

719
01:04:06,384 --> 01:04:07,684
Where's my brother?

720
01:04:09,346 --> 01:04:11,176
Your brother is right here.

721
01:04:49,010 --> 01:04:51,350
That old man is
the founder of this hospital.

722
01:04:51,721 --> 01:04:54,221
He's acquainted with Yu-na's dad,
so I even introduced myself.

723
01:04:55,308 --> 01:04:56,978
Do you know what's uncanny?

724
01:04:57,060 --> 01:04:59,230
He has the same name as you.

725
01:04:59,687 --> 01:05:00,937
His name is Ji Hyeon-jung.

726
01:05:04,734 --> 01:05:06,034
<i>Hyeon-jung.</i>

727
01:05:08,696 --> 01:05:10,736
What is it? Do your legs hurt?

728
01:05:13,201 --> 01:05:15,751
Do you want a piggyback ride? Come here.

729
01:05:22,001 --> 01:05:24,881
How much do you like me?

730
01:05:25,046 --> 01:05:26,336
This much.

731
01:05:26,423 --> 01:05:28,093
That's so little.

732
01:05:28,633 --> 01:05:30,053
This much.

733
01:05:30,718 --> 01:05:33,428
That much? As many as your loose teeth?

734
01:05:42,105 --> 01:05:45,355
Ji Hyeon-jung.

735
01:05:49,612 --> 01:05:53,492
I'm sorry. I wasn't calling you.

736
01:05:54,075 --> 01:05:55,485
I'm sorry.

737
01:05:56,453 --> 01:05:57,583
Ji Hyeon...

738
01:05:58,496 --> 01:06:00,496
Jung. What is this?

739
01:06:02,542 --> 01:06:05,922
He always disappears
without saying a thing.

740
01:06:12,135 --> 01:06:15,965
Hyeon-jung's little sister is
quite old now.

741
01:06:16,764 --> 01:06:19,734
I heard that she lost her vision
and that her health deteriorated.

742
01:06:20,477 --> 01:06:23,977
I guess we're going to
see Hyeon-jung off pretty soon.

743
01:06:33,072 --> 01:06:35,582
Will they all get on the bus
to the afterlife today?

744
01:06:35,909 --> 01:06:38,949
You go first. We'll go later.

745
01:06:39,454 --> 01:06:42,174
I'll leave first. You can come later.

746
01:06:42,916 --> 01:06:46,086
I got to live with my first love
all my life.

747
01:06:46,169 --> 01:06:49,339
So you should make your first love
come true here too.

748
01:06:49,839 --> 01:06:51,549
You can leave then without any regrets.

749
01:06:53,301 --> 01:06:55,511
Thank you for everything. Take care.

750
01:07:01,601 --> 01:07:04,771
The platform is this way.

751
01:07:25,875 --> 01:07:26,955
You look upset.

752
01:07:28,586 --> 01:07:30,796
My sister is upset too,

753
01:07:30,880 --> 01:07:33,800
saying it was impudent
of you two to test us.

754
01:07:35,510 --> 01:07:37,050
We would've welcomed you

755
01:07:37,136 --> 01:07:39,176
if you came looking like that
in front of our guest.

756
01:07:39,264 --> 01:07:41,814
If we start showing up
in the way they want,

757
01:07:42,141 --> 01:07:44,851
they'll stop putting
in any efforts themselves.

758
01:07:48,273 --> 01:07:51,033
You must be doing a good job.

759
01:07:51,317 --> 01:07:53,567
I think the flower will bloom.

760
01:07:58,741 --> 01:08:00,991
You should look after it well

761
01:08:01,578 --> 01:08:03,578
so you can send her off.

762
01:08:06,291 --> 01:08:07,631
Isn't it beautiful?

763
01:08:12,338 --> 01:08:13,878
The sea looks really beautiful.

764
01:08:15,633 --> 01:08:16,723
Yes, indeed.

765
01:08:20,680 --> 01:08:21,760
It makes me sad.

766
01:08:24,892 --> 01:08:26,022
It's beautiful.

767
01:08:27,645 --> 01:08:28,805
It makes me sad.

768
01:08:40,700 --> 01:08:43,370
<i>The funds that Jeong Eun-seok concealed
were found.</i>

769
01:08:43,453 --> 01:08:46,003
<i>It was discovered at a sunflower field</i>

770
01:08:46,080 --> 01:08:47,540
<i>near Jeong's hometown.</i>

771
01:08:47,624 --> 01:08:49,424
<i>About 4 billion won in 50,000-won bills...</i>

772
01:08:49,500 --> 01:08:52,710
He asked us if we were
reporters or police officers

773
01:08:52,795 --> 01:08:56,005
{\an8}because he was doing
something illegal like that.

774
01:08:56,841 --> 01:09:00,601
By the way, the owner of that field
must be someone stupid like you.

775
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:02,600
If he finds four billion won in cash,

776
01:09:02,680 --> 01:09:05,600
he should keep it. Why did he report it?

777
01:09:05,683 --> 01:09:07,853
My goodness.

778
01:09:09,395 --> 01:09:12,475
This must be why he had a picture
of a sunflower field in his office.

779
01:09:12,940 --> 01:09:13,780
What?

780
01:09:14,942 --> 01:09:17,242
Don't you remember?
You took a picture of it.

781
01:09:18,237 --> 01:09:20,907
That's why he acted so sensitive
when you took those pictures.

782
01:09:21,115 --> 01:09:22,115
Pictures?

783
01:09:24,994 --> 01:09:26,254
That's enough.

784
01:09:39,842 --> 01:09:41,052
No way.

785
01:09:41,761 --> 01:09:43,811
A field of money was right before my eyes,

786
01:09:44,222 --> 01:09:45,812
and I had no idea.

787
01:09:46,265 --> 01:09:49,225
That's what I should've asked him.

788
01:09:50,520 --> 01:09:51,850
My sunflower field.

789
01:09:52,355 --> 01:09:54,395
{\an8}POLICE TO INVESTIGATE
CONNECTION TO JEONG'S DEATH

790
01:09:54,607 --> 01:09:56,477
My four billion won!

791
01:09:56,567 --> 01:09:58,237
How is that your money?

792
01:09:58,569 --> 01:10:00,609
That's a ridiculous claim of ownership.

793
01:10:03,199 --> 01:10:04,199
My money.

794
01:10:09,914 --> 01:10:12,334
Chan-sung went out to sail on my yacht
with his boss.

795
01:10:12,500 --> 01:10:14,250
He said he should calm his angry boss.

796
01:10:15,169 --> 01:10:18,209
Chan-sung is sailing on a yacht
with his boss?

797
01:10:19,298 --> 01:10:21,338
Is he entertaining his boss?

798
01:10:21,426 --> 01:10:24,096
I wouldn't call it entertaining.
It's more like a date.

799
01:10:30,601 --> 01:10:32,851
I lost four billion won
right in front of my eyes.

800
01:10:33,354 --> 01:10:35,944
I'm in no mood to ride
someone else's yacht.

801
01:10:36,733 --> 01:10:39,403
Like I said, that money isn't yours.

802
01:10:39,485 --> 01:10:42,445
How can you say that
just because you have a picture of it?

803
01:10:43,114 --> 01:10:44,124
Forget it.

804
01:10:44,741 --> 01:10:47,791
Can't you just console me

805
01:10:48,077 --> 01:10:49,827
even if you don't mean it?

806
01:10:49,912 --> 01:10:52,212
"Would you like me to buy you a yacht?"

807
01:10:52,415 --> 01:10:53,825
You could say something like this.

808
01:10:53,916 --> 01:10:55,376
Why are you getting on my nerves?

809
01:10:55,960 --> 01:10:58,300
I'll buy you a yacht then.

810
01:11:07,680 --> 01:11:10,220
Here. Now that you have a picture,
it's yours.

811
01:11:13,895 --> 01:11:16,895
You are a thief
if you want something that's not yours.

812
01:11:16,981 --> 01:11:19,151
I am a thief.

813
01:11:19,275 --> 01:11:20,605
Didn't you see in your dream?

814
01:11:20,693 --> 01:11:22,863
Your people were all thieves?

815
01:11:23,654 --> 01:11:26,994
The man who married you
looked like he had a higher status.

816
01:11:27,241 --> 01:11:29,581
Married? Me?

817
01:11:35,124 --> 01:11:37,344
<i>I saw you wearing a red bridal dress.</i>

818
01:11:40,254 --> 01:11:43,134
Since it looked fancy,
I assumed you married someone

819
01:11:43,216 --> 01:11:44,546
with some nobleman.

820
01:11:46,260 --> 01:11:47,260
I was...

821
01:11:48,262 --> 01:11:50,062
wearing someone else's dress.

822
01:12:04,278 --> 01:12:05,398
Chan-sung.

823
01:12:07,865 --> 01:12:09,405
I was a bad person.

824
01:12:10,243 --> 01:12:11,873
I'm still bad now,

825
01:12:12,495 --> 01:12:14,365
but I was a lot worse before.

826
01:12:15,957 --> 01:12:17,577
Since you can see my past,

827
01:12:18,709 --> 01:12:20,709
you'll gradually find out

828
01:12:21,963 --> 01:12:23,553
how much of a horrible person I was.

829
01:12:38,646 --> 01:12:39,686
What is it?

830
01:12:41,482 --> 01:12:42,402
Where?

831
01:13:35,953 --> 01:13:37,203
Chan-sung.

832
01:13:37,914 --> 01:13:39,004
Hey, Mi-ra.

833
01:15:06,877 --> 01:15:09,087
{\an8}<i>Are there more secrets
in this hotel I'm not aware of?</i>

834
01:15:09,171 --> 01:15:12,841
{\an8}<i>Ms. Jang can never leave this hotel.</i>

835
01:15:12,925 --> 01:15:14,175
{\an8}<i>Let's do nice things together.</i>

836
01:15:14,260 --> 01:15:17,140
{\an8}It's better to see
and eat good things together.

837
01:15:17,430 --> 01:15:19,270
{\an8}<i>What I have is hell.</i>

838
01:15:19,348 --> 01:15:22,638
{\an8}It's not that wonderful
to be in hell together.

839
01:15:22,727 --> 01:15:24,017
{\an8}Just let her pass by.

840
01:15:24,103 --> 01:15:26,773
{\an8}<i>How could I just let her pass by?</i>

841
01:15:26,856 --> 01:15:27,766
{\an8}Don't do it.

842
01:15:27,857 --> 01:15:29,437
{\an8}<i>Run away from me, Chan-sung.</i>

843
01:15:29,525 --> 01:15:32,275
{\an8}<i>I don't care if this is
your prison or your fence.</i>

844
01:15:32,445 --> 01:15:35,275
{\an8}<i>I will stay here with you.</i>

845
01:15:35,990 --> 01:15:37,990
{\an8}Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu

846
01:17:06,130 --> 01:17:07,260
Cheong-myeong, is that you?

847
01:17:26,150 --> 01:17:27,860
You look happy,

848
01:17:29,361 --> 01:17:30,531
Princess Song-hwa.

849
01:17:44,001 --> 01:17:45,291
FULL MOON

850
01:17:50,090 --> 01:17:51,800
Why are you here?

851
01:17:52,384 --> 01:17:53,684
Why do you think?

852
01:17:55,095 --> 01:17:57,635
Do you think I came here
to congratulate your wedding?

853
01:17:59,349 --> 01:18:01,849
I shouldn't have shown you
mercy back then.

854
01:18:03,270 --> 01:18:05,560
The big smile you had on your face earlier

855
01:18:06,523 --> 01:18:08,193
was very beautiful.

856
01:18:10,193 --> 01:18:11,573
What a pity.

857
01:18:12,613 --> 01:18:14,453
The groom is never going to see it.

858
01:18:17,492 --> 01:18:19,242
I'll greet him in your stead.

859
01:18:20,621 --> 01:18:22,541
My smile might not look beautiful, though.

860
01:19:04,373 --> 01:19:05,543
Chan-sung.

861
01:19:06,333 --> 01:19:07,463
Hey, Mi-ra.

862
01:19:12,756 --> 01:19:16,126
She's my friend.
I wonder how she knew I'd be here.

863
01:19:17,386 --> 01:19:18,636
Chan-sung.

864
01:19:21,181 --> 01:19:23,101
You brought her here.

865
01:19:24,476 --> 01:19:26,936
I'm sorry for making you uncomfortable.

866
01:19:27,896 --> 01:19:29,646
This is why you came.

867
01:19:32,734 --> 01:19:35,034
They had no intention of letting me go...

868
01:19:36,655 --> 01:19:38,565
from the beginning.

869
01:19:39,241 --> 01:19:40,491
Jang Man-wol.

870
01:19:41,285 --> 01:19:42,575
Is there something wrong?

871
01:19:48,583 --> 01:19:50,253
She's smiling again...

872
01:19:52,421 --> 01:19:54,051
right in front of me.

873
01:20:07,394 --> 01:20:08,734
Gosh, Mi-ra!

874
01:20:28,665 --> 01:20:30,075
Go look after her.

875
01:20:31,543 --> 01:20:33,133
That is your job.

876
01:20:48,143 --> 01:20:49,233
Here.

877
01:20:54,941 --> 01:20:57,361
-Hey, Chan-sung.
-Oh, sorry.

878
01:20:58,070 --> 01:20:59,610
-Hold my hand.
-Okay.

879
01:21:20,425 --> 01:21:21,425
Here.

880
01:21:22,469 --> 01:21:23,719
Thanks.

881
01:21:23,804 --> 01:21:24,854
Well...

882
01:21:25,388 --> 01:21:27,468
I did come to bother you,

883
01:21:27,808 --> 01:21:30,058
but I didn't know
I'd end up doing it this way.

884
01:21:32,312 --> 01:21:33,402
Drink this.

885
01:21:33,855 --> 01:21:36,105
You drank seawater earlier.
It'll refresh you.

886
01:21:41,947 --> 01:21:43,617
Was her name Jang Man-wol?

887
01:21:44,199 --> 01:21:46,199
Your boss. Did she leave because of me?

888
01:21:47,244 --> 01:21:48,414
Do you know her by any chance?

889
01:21:48,495 --> 01:21:50,205
No, I've never seen her before.

890
01:21:50,455 --> 01:21:52,205
Why do you ask? Did she say she knows me?

891
01:21:53,250 --> 01:21:54,790
Did I see her at the hospital?

892
01:21:56,503 --> 01:21:59,173
Anyway, I'm being such a nuisance.

893
01:21:59,422 --> 01:22:01,592
By the way,
that was not intentional at all.

894
01:22:01,675 --> 01:22:04,335
The wind blew suddenly
as if someone was pushing me.

895
01:22:04,886 --> 01:22:06,636
My gosh, that was so scary.

896
01:22:14,688 --> 01:22:16,398
Was it she who did that?

897
01:22:17,649 --> 01:22:21,449
Nothing's been going my way.
I must be cursed or something.

898
01:22:21,820 --> 01:22:23,280
Should I go see a shaman?

899
01:22:23,822 --> 01:22:25,032
You need to sprinkle salt.

900
01:22:26,408 --> 01:22:28,698
You must purify yourself
when evil ghosts are bugging you.

901
01:22:28,869 --> 01:22:32,459
Don't stay out until late at night
just in case, and try not to be alone.

902
01:22:32,539 --> 01:22:35,129
You sound just like my grandma right now.

903
01:22:35,417 --> 01:22:38,167
She always used to say
that I must be careful at all times

904
01:22:38,253 --> 01:22:40,673
because of my bad karma
from my past lives.

905
01:22:41,214 --> 01:22:43,974
She gave me this.
She said it'll protect me.

906
01:22:44,634 --> 01:22:46,014
You still wear that bracelet?

907
01:22:47,345 --> 01:22:48,805
You remember it.

908
01:22:49,931 --> 01:22:52,141
Chan-sung, I think bad ghosts are
following me around.

909
01:22:52,225 --> 01:22:54,975
-Stay with me at night.
-I have to work at night.

910
01:22:55,061 --> 01:22:57,271
I called a cab for you,
so just go home when it comes.

911
01:22:57,355 --> 01:22:59,265
I lost my purse though.

912
01:22:59,357 --> 01:23:00,777
I've already paid for the cab ride.

913
01:23:00,859 --> 01:23:02,569
I'll put it on your tab, so pay me back.

914
01:23:02,652 --> 01:23:05,822
Don't forget that you're in debt,
which is even scarier than ghosts.

915
01:23:09,117 --> 01:23:10,197
Gosh.

916
01:23:12,370 --> 01:23:13,370
My gosh.

917
01:23:16,708 --> 01:23:18,038
Chan-sung.

918
01:23:18,919 --> 01:23:20,959
You brought her here.

919
01:23:21,713 --> 01:23:23,633
This is why you came.

920
01:23:28,303 --> 01:23:29,893
I wonder if she's okay.

921
01:23:53,954 --> 01:23:56,794
LEE MI-RA

922
01:23:57,999 --> 01:23:59,249
"Lee Mi-ra."

923
01:24:37,455 --> 01:24:40,375
She's the girl he used to date
back when he was in the States.

924
01:24:47,048 --> 01:24:49,258
What a cruel twist of fate.

925
01:24:51,052 --> 01:24:52,892
Enough is enough, please.

926
01:24:53,763 --> 01:24:54,763
DELETE ONE IMAGE

927
01:25:04,065 --> 01:25:06,065
Gosh, how much longer
will you folks keep that up?

928
01:25:08,570 --> 01:25:09,990
Let's go!

929
01:25:16,786 --> 01:25:19,326
I have a lot on my mind right now.

930
01:25:19,414 --> 01:25:22,674
Those ridiculous dance moves are
really getting on my nerves.

931
01:25:22,751 --> 01:25:25,211
Enough, okay?

932
01:25:27,172 --> 01:25:28,882
This is nice!

933
01:25:29,090 --> 01:25:30,720
My gosh, so nice!

934
01:25:41,102 --> 01:25:42,192
Next news.

935
01:25:42,270 --> 01:25:45,400
Ms. Park Heung-ja,
the oldest living person in the country...

936
01:25:45,482 --> 01:25:46,902
You folks can

937
01:25:47,984 --> 01:25:50,324
take a break and start dancing away again
after I get off.

938
01:25:50,570 --> 01:25:54,200
She was the only living person
in the country born in the 19th century.

939
01:25:54,282 --> 01:25:57,242
Ms. Park lived to be 120
and led a happy life

940
01:25:57,327 --> 01:26:00,747
with her children and grandchildren,
always offering positive words of wisdom

941
01:26:00,830 --> 01:26:02,080
with a smile on her face.

942
01:26:02,165 --> 01:26:05,335
She led a great life
and passed away with no regrets.

943
01:26:10,048 --> 01:26:12,798
IN MOURNING

944
01:26:17,806 --> 01:26:20,346
You've enjoyed a fortunate life
for over a century,

945
01:26:20,517 --> 01:26:22,227
so you can leave with no regrets.

946
01:26:30,693 --> 01:26:32,073
You're going to leave like this?

947
01:26:39,411 --> 01:26:42,041
Your great-grandson's wife is due
quite soon.

948
01:26:42,122 --> 01:26:46,462
Wait a couple of months, and you can meet
your great-great-grandchild.

949
01:26:46,793 --> 01:26:48,673
She lived for 120 years.

950
01:26:48,753 --> 01:26:51,973
She has 8 children and 24 grandchildren.

951
01:26:52,048 --> 01:26:54,428
It'd be foolishly greedy of her
to stay just to meet

952
01:26:54,509 --> 01:26:56,259
her great-great-grandchild.

953
01:26:56,428 --> 01:27:00,058
Your great-great-grandchild will be
so adorable.

954
01:27:00,140 --> 01:27:03,270
You'll be incredibly sad
if you don't get to meet this baby.

955
01:27:03,601 --> 01:27:05,481
I said, she lived for 120 years.

956
01:27:07,313 --> 01:27:08,903
You have nothing to be sad about.

957
01:27:19,200 --> 01:27:23,750
Why stop a soul
who is ready to rest in peace?

958
01:27:24,789 --> 01:27:27,209
I stopped her?
No, her great-great-grandkid did.

959
01:27:28,460 --> 01:27:29,920
She has witnessed three centuries

960
01:27:30,003 --> 01:27:33,263
and experienced everything
humans could possibly experience

961
01:27:33,339 --> 01:27:34,799
in one lifetime.

962
01:27:35,049 --> 01:27:37,049
And because of you, that special soul will

963
01:27:37,343 --> 01:27:39,103
wander around the realm of the living now.

964
01:27:39,179 --> 01:27:42,389
They won't let such a special soul
wander around.

965
01:27:44,350 --> 01:27:47,100
Look, that nosy woman is already here.

966
01:28:08,166 --> 01:28:10,996
Her children are great cooks.

967
01:28:11,127 --> 01:28:13,167
This funeral food is really delicious.

968
01:28:13,588 --> 01:28:15,968
Hey, try some.

969
01:28:18,843 --> 01:28:21,433
I can tell right away
it came out of frozen ready meals.

970
01:28:22,347 --> 01:28:24,637
If you have to cook yourself
for the funeral,

971
01:28:24,724 --> 01:28:27,564
your family will never be at peace.
That's how it is these days.

972
01:28:28,645 --> 01:28:32,685
I guess her family's motto is
to take the easy way.

973
01:28:32,857 --> 01:28:35,897
This is why her family was so happy.

974
01:28:38,071 --> 01:28:39,741
Did you interrupt

975
01:28:39,822 --> 01:28:42,282
that soul's journey
to the afterlife just to see me?

976
01:28:44,077 --> 01:28:45,577
I'm kind of regretting it.

977
01:28:46,371 --> 01:28:47,501
It's too much of a hassle.

978
01:28:48,498 --> 01:28:50,418
I should have gone to her right away.

979
01:28:52,710 --> 01:28:54,380
To that woman, Song-hwa.

980
01:28:57,924 --> 01:29:01,144
No, in this life, she's Lee Mi-ra.

981
01:29:01,803 --> 01:29:04,513
While you were shriveled up
and your time stopped,

982
01:29:05,640 --> 01:29:09,020
she came back to this life
as a human after living many lives.

983
01:29:10,520 --> 01:29:13,270
You have met due to the connection
in your previous life.

984
01:29:13,356 --> 01:29:15,186
Just let her pass by.

985
01:29:15,942 --> 01:29:19,112
How could I just let her pass by?

986
01:29:22,699 --> 01:29:26,199
To you, she may be an object
of an unresolved grudge.

987
01:29:26,995 --> 01:29:28,325
To her,

988
01:29:28,997 --> 01:29:32,127
you're a piece of her previous lives
that she doesn't even remember.

989
01:29:34,210 --> 01:29:36,630
You wanted me to let her pass by.

990
01:29:38,089 --> 01:29:41,009
That's why you made me meet her
through Chan-sung.

991
01:29:43,052 --> 01:29:46,602
You cannot harm that girl.

992
01:29:52,687 --> 01:29:55,317
Only if I let her pass by,
I could leave this world peacefully.

993
01:29:57,108 --> 01:30:01,068
Just like the warmhearted Mago wants.

994
01:30:12,582 --> 01:30:14,212
To give you some relief,

995
01:30:15,084 --> 01:30:18,004
I'll go back to the hotel
without causing trouble and stay there.

996
01:30:27,639 --> 01:30:28,809
Drop me off on your way.

997
01:30:29,766 --> 01:30:32,016
Or you can take me to the Samdo River.

998
01:30:45,073 --> 01:30:46,123
Will...

999
01:30:48,743 --> 01:30:49,743
he come too?

1000
01:31:17,146 --> 01:31:20,816
For a flower to blossom,
she needs to feel the wind

1001
01:31:21,192 --> 01:31:22,822
and face the rain too.

1002
01:31:32,453 --> 01:31:34,163
Do you know where Ms. Jang is?

1003
01:31:35,665 --> 01:31:37,535
She hasn't come back yet.

1004
01:31:37,625 --> 01:31:39,415
Did anything happen on your outing?

1005
01:31:39,627 --> 01:31:41,917
She got mad all of a sudden
and disappeared.

1006
01:31:42,005 --> 01:31:45,045
Ms. Jang's sudden change of mood
isn't special.

1007
01:31:45,133 --> 01:31:46,433
It happens all the time.

1008
01:31:46,551 --> 01:31:49,391
When she gets mad, she usually
goes shopping or to a restaurant.

1009
01:31:49,470 --> 01:31:52,390
She's probably at a department store
or at a famous restaurant now.

1010
01:31:52,473 --> 01:31:55,143
She probably can't do that
because her credit card's maxed out.

1011
01:31:55,226 --> 01:31:57,596
Then, she must be livid.

1012
01:31:57,687 --> 01:31:59,897
I should stay away from her today.

1013
01:31:59,981 --> 01:32:02,691
When she gets livid,
does she vanish into thin air

1014
01:32:02,775 --> 01:32:03,985
and not come back to the hotel?

1015
01:32:04,068 --> 01:32:05,448
That never happens.

1016
01:32:05,528 --> 01:32:07,738
Ms. Jang has to come back to the hotel.

1017
01:32:07,822 --> 01:32:10,032
No matter how far she runs away,
the hotel will chase after her.

1018
01:32:10,658 --> 01:32:12,328
The hotel will chase after her?

1019
01:32:17,123 --> 01:32:19,383
Are there more secrets
in this hotel I'm not aware of?

1020
01:32:19,459 --> 01:32:21,169
If Ms. Jang didn't tell you,

1021
01:32:21,252 --> 01:32:23,052
-you don't--
-I don't have to know?

1022
01:32:25,173 --> 01:32:28,633
I'm not here to stay
just temporarily anymore.

1023
01:32:29,218 --> 01:32:31,508
If all the hotel staff knows what it is,

1024
01:32:31,929 --> 01:32:33,179
I must know too.

1025
01:32:36,934 --> 01:32:39,854
You said that she was tied down
to this hotel for a punishment.

1026
01:32:39,937 --> 01:32:42,897
Does her punishment follow after her
when she runs away from it?

1027
01:32:43,191 --> 01:32:44,191
That's right.

1028
01:32:44,901 --> 01:32:49,491
Ms. Jang can never leave this hotel.

1029
01:33:13,554 --> 01:33:15,434
She can't go to the afterlife.

1030
01:33:17,058 --> 01:33:19,018
And she can't live in this world either.

1031
01:33:20,186 --> 01:33:23,556
It looks like she tried several times
to run away at first.

1032
01:33:24,649 --> 01:33:25,979
But it never worked.

1033
01:33:31,197 --> 01:33:33,827
Ms. Jang is the Moon Tree.

1034
01:33:34,075 --> 01:33:37,285
And the energy of the Moon Tree
is creating this space.

1035
01:33:40,331 --> 01:33:43,921
Wherever she goes,
the Moon Tree will put down roots there.

1036
01:33:44,502 --> 01:33:47,632
And there stands
the Guest House of the Moon.

1037
01:34:05,523 --> 01:34:08,113
When she stays away from the hotel
for more than a day,

1038
01:34:08,526 --> 01:34:11,776
the Moon Tree follows her to where she is.

1039
01:34:12,196 --> 01:34:14,116
That's why she must return.

1040
01:34:15,074 --> 01:34:17,294
It's impossible for her to escape from it.

1041
01:34:20,830 --> 01:34:21,830
That means

1042
01:34:22,748 --> 01:34:24,828
she's been locked up in this hotel.

1043
01:34:29,380 --> 01:34:31,760
But why was she tied down here?

1044
01:34:33,384 --> 01:34:35,304
I heard
that she almost became an evil ghost,

1045
01:34:35,386 --> 01:34:38,136
but Mago brought her here
and tied her down to this place.

1046
01:34:38,222 --> 01:34:41,022
You've seen what happened

1047
01:34:41,100 --> 01:34:44,150
to the vengeful ghost
who harmed humans in this life.

1048
01:34:51,736 --> 01:34:56,656
To Ms. Jang, this may be her prison,
but it's also a fence.

1049
01:34:58,159 --> 01:35:00,119
It's safe for her to stay here.

1050
01:35:13,299 --> 01:35:14,299
Here.

1051
01:35:14,759 --> 01:35:15,969
Thank you.

1052
01:35:16,052 --> 01:35:17,932
You were lucky. No one took your bag.

1053
01:35:18,012 --> 01:35:19,142
Thank you so much.

1054
01:35:24,518 --> 01:35:26,768
How did this end up on the bus?

1055
01:35:29,523 --> 01:35:30,403
Wait.

1056
01:35:33,361 --> 01:35:34,861
My photo is missing.

1057
01:35:38,866 --> 01:35:40,906
Amusement park.

1058
01:35:42,453 --> 01:35:44,873
It looks like Lee Mi-ra was happy.

1059
01:35:54,924 --> 01:35:56,094
Chan-sung?

1060
01:36:15,861 --> 01:36:18,821
Mr. Koo told me to prepare this for you.

1061
01:36:21,450 --> 01:36:24,660
He was quite worried
when you didn't come back

1062
01:36:24,829 --> 01:36:26,409
after you disappeared without a word.

1063
01:36:29,542 --> 01:36:31,292
I met someone,

1064
01:36:32,461 --> 01:36:34,131
and I needed some time to think alone.

1065
01:36:34,255 --> 01:36:35,455
As he was worried,

1066
01:36:35,548 --> 01:36:40,338
I told him why you had no choice
but to come back to the hotel.

1067
01:36:44,640 --> 01:36:45,640
You did?

1068
01:36:46,934 --> 01:36:48,644
Where's Chan-sung now?

1069
01:37:05,703 --> 01:37:06,793
Is she okay?

1070
01:37:12,168 --> 01:37:13,338
Your friend.

1071
01:37:14,211 --> 01:37:16,051
I made her fall into the water.

1072
01:37:16,380 --> 01:37:17,720
Did she drown?

1073
01:37:19,258 --> 01:37:20,468
She's fine.

1074
01:37:20,843 --> 01:37:21,933
Too bad.

1075
01:37:32,855 --> 01:37:34,145
Why aren't you asking me

1076
01:37:36,525 --> 01:37:38,235
why I made her fall into the water

1077
01:37:38,319 --> 01:37:40,199
and what I saw in her face?

1078
01:37:40,279 --> 01:37:42,779
You should ask me millions of questions,
scold me, and stop me.

1079
01:37:43,282 --> 01:37:46,292
If I try to stop you, will that work?

1080
01:37:52,208 --> 01:37:53,708
I really don't know.

1081
01:37:54,585 --> 01:37:57,245
You call yourself a really bad person.

1082
01:37:58,214 --> 01:38:00,304
And seeing how you've been stuck here
for 1,000 years,

1083
01:38:00,674 --> 01:38:02,434
I guess you did something very serious.

1084
01:38:05,554 --> 01:38:07,474
When I saw you in my dream,

1085
01:38:08,474 --> 01:38:10,024
you were just in love.

1086
01:38:16,941 --> 01:38:18,151
So what did you do earlier?

1087
01:38:19,485 --> 01:38:20,395
What?

1088
01:38:21,320 --> 01:38:24,160
Where did you go after ditching me?

1089
01:38:24,657 --> 01:38:26,987
There's nothing much for you to do
with a maxed-out credit card.

1090
01:38:28,786 --> 01:38:32,536
I don't need you or my credit card
to have fun, you know.

1091
01:38:32,623 --> 01:38:34,543
I attended a dance party

1092
01:38:35,709 --> 01:38:37,459
and ate nice food at a feast.

1093
01:38:38,921 --> 01:38:39,921
A dance party?

1094
01:38:40,005 --> 01:38:44,005
Yes, the dance moves were
really mysterious.

1095
01:38:46,470 --> 01:38:48,470
And you went there alone?

1096
01:38:48,597 --> 01:38:51,097
You could've invited me. Unbelievable.

1097
01:38:52,893 --> 01:38:54,523
If you were there,

1098
01:38:55,479 --> 01:38:56,939
it would've been a sight.

1099
01:39:00,401 --> 01:39:02,281
Let's do nice things together.

1100
01:39:03,028 --> 01:39:06,738
It's better to see
and eat good things together.

1101
01:39:09,952 --> 01:39:13,622
The view is much better
now that I'm with you.

1102
01:39:39,648 --> 01:39:41,228
Whatever it is you're going to do,

1103
01:39:42,109 --> 01:39:43,489
just don't forget this.

1104
01:39:45,738 --> 01:39:48,658
I don't care if this is
your prison or your fence.

1105
01:39:50,284 --> 01:39:51,244
I will...

1106
01:39:53,245 --> 01:39:54,745
stay here with you.

1107
01:41:40,811 --> 01:41:41,901
Doctor.

1108
01:41:48,777 --> 01:41:51,697
Sir, it's raining.

1109
01:41:56,243 --> 01:41:58,453
I'm always happy whenever it rains

1110
01:41:58,912 --> 01:42:00,582
because I'll be with you.

1111
01:42:03,584 --> 01:42:05,094
I'm not your doctor, miss.

1112
01:42:05,627 --> 01:42:08,837
Please stay with me until the song ends.

1113
01:42:35,489 --> 01:42:36,409
Honey?

1114
01:42:46,375 --> 01:42:50,375
Honey?

1115
01:43:04,726 --> 01:43:05,596
Hey.

1116
01:43:05,685 --> 01:43:06,515
Hey.

1117
01:43:12,067 --> 01:43:12,897
What's that?

1118
01:43:14,111 --> 01:43:16,321
You're the one who said
she should stay with us.

1119
01:43:17,072 --> 01:43:19,322
Me? To whom?

1120
01:43:19,449 --> 01:43:20,529
Me.

1121
01:43:23,412 --> 01:43:25,502
What are you doing here?

1122
01:43:26,081 --> 01:43:28,081
I was scared to be alone.

1123
01:43:28,166 --> 01:43:30,286
You have no idea what happened to me.

1124
01:43:31,002 --> 01:43:33,802
-What happened?
-I found the purse I had lost

1125
01:43:33,880 --> 01:43:35,260
on an express bus

1126
01:43:36,383 --> 01:43:38,593
when I never got on one.

1127
01:43:38,802 --> 01:43:43,062
Hold on. Does this mean
that it got on the bus itself?

1128
01:43:43,348 --> 01:43:44,468
My gosh!

1129
01:43:45,392 --> 01:43:46,692
Stop it, both of you.

1130
01:43:46,893 --> 01:43:48,773
When I'm home, I'd like a rest
from the supernatural.

1131
01:43:48,854 --> 01:43:51,064
But this can't be explained
scientifically.

1132
01:43:51,356 --> 01:43:54,646
Someone must've taken your purse
and left it on the bus.

1133
01:43:55,986 --> 01:43:58,486
Yes, that's possible. You're right.

1134
01:43:59,448 --> 01:44:01,868
Didn't you lose anything?
Money or credit cards?

1135
01:44:01,950 --> 01:44:03,580
I never carried around any.

1136
01:44:04,161 --> 01:44:06,331
That being said, can I borrow some money?

1137
01:44:09,249 --> 01:44:10,579
Sanchez!

1138
01:44:13,295 --> 01:44:15,335
I'll let her stay here for now,
just in case.

1139
01:44:18,675 --> 01:44:20,795
You're opening
the hotel's amusement park again?

1140
01:44:21,011 --> 01:44:24,891
Yes, someone seems to have had
some fond memories of an amusement park.

1141
01:44:42,741 --> 01:44:45,871
Whoever it is,
the guest will have fun here.

1142
01:44:46,077 --> 01:44:47,537
So when will that guest arrive?

1143
01:44:48,955 --> 01:44:50,075
I'll invite her soon.

1144
01:44:51,625 --> 01:44:53,335
Escort her with care.

1145
01:44:53,418 --> 01:44:54,418
Yes, ma'am.

1146
01:44:54,961 --> 01:44:58,341
By the way, where did you send
Mr. Kim and Ms. Choe?

1147
01:44:59,132 --> 01:45:00,222
To seek out some land.

1148
01:45:08,266 --> 01:45:10,226
It's eerie and full of negative energy.

1149
01:45:10,310 --> 01:45:12,350
There aren't any buildings
in the way either.

1150
01:45:12,437 --> 01:45:13,397
I like this place.

1151
01:45:13,772 --> 01:45:15,772
There aren't
any shopping malls or restaurants

1152
01:45:15,857 --> 01:45:17,107
within a 15-minute drive.

1153
01:45:17,192 --> 01:45:18,782
Ms. Jang won't like it.

1154
01:45:19,194 --> 01:45:20,074
Let's leave

1155
01:45:20,153 --> 01:45:23,573
and head over to the next candidate,
a sauna building.

1156
01:45:23,740 --> 01:45:26,280
Why is she suddenly looking to buy land?

1157
01:45:26,368 --> 01:45:29,578
It seems she can barely
pay off her credit card bills.

1158
01:45:29,663 --> 01:45:32,463
You're right.
Unless she sells the land she has.

1159
01:45:34,251 --> 01:45:37,001
No way. Ms. Jang loves that land.

1160
01:45:37,087 --> 01:45:39,967
It's very close to a department store
and naengmyeon restaurants.

1161
01:45:41,299 --> 01:45:44,549
But then again, Chan-sung is being
too tight with money.

1162
01:45:44,636 --> 01:45:46,386
So it might be possible.

1163
01:45:46,888 --> 01:45:49,718
She chose that land
after much consideration.

1164
01:45:49,808 --> 01:45:51,888
There's no way she'd sell it. Let's go.

1165
01:45:52,727 --> 01:45:54,897
Eunseong Sauna.

1166
01:45:55,105 --> 01:45:56,105
EUNSEONG SAUNA

1167
01:45:59,317 --> 01:46:02,527
You're very quick
to master new features on devices.

1168
01:46:02,612 --> 01:46:05,162
You get the hang of it
after clicking here and there.

1169
01:46:05,782 --> 01:46:07,872
I can't, since I'm from
the Joseon Dynasty.

1170
01:46:07,951 --> 01:46:09,791
I am from that era, too.

1171
01:46:09,870 --> 01:46:11,750
You should correct how you speak first.

1172
01:46:11,830 --> 01:46:15,040
Until when will you use archaic phrases?

1173
01:46:20,171 --> 01:46:21,761
I'll try my best.

1174
01:46:22,257 --> 01:46:23,837
Wait for me.

1175
01:46:24,092 --> 01:46:25,342
Hold up.

1176
01:46:25,844 --> 01:46:27,104
Thank you for the tour!

1177
01:46:32,392 --> 01:46:33,772
Thanks, man.

1178
01:46:33,852 --> 01:46:36,652
We'll totally contact you
after talking to our boss.

1179
01:46:49,284 --> 01:46:51,334
The hotel opened up an amusement park?

1180
01:46:51,995 --> 01:46:53,785
Yes, you should check it out.

1181
01:46:54,998 --> 01:46:58,878
It'll be fun to go there
with my boyfriend.

1182
01:46:59,044 --> 01:47:00,344
Did you get a boyfriend?

1183
01:47:02,464 --> 01:47:04,804
Rumors about me having one are
all over the school.

1184
01:47:04,883 --> 01:47:07,143
Is that so? Good for you.

1185
01:47:07,218 --> 01:47:09,598
You have a boyfriend now,
so keep up with your studies

1186
01:47:09,679 --> 01:47:11,559
and go to classes on time. Okay?

1187
01:47:11,848 --> 01:47:12,768
Whatever!

1188
01:47:12,849 --> 01:47:15,889
You really liked to go to school.
How could you become a total idiot?

1189
01:47:16,269 --> 01:47:18,939
What's wrong with telling you
to study hard at school?

1190
01:47:19,230 --> 01:47:20,570
It would be nice to study hard

1191
01:47:20,857 --> 01:47:24,147
and become a cool doctor
just like Mr. Koo's girlfriend.

1192
01:47:24,694 --> 01:47:28,704
Ms. Jang told me to keep an eye on her
and find out what people think of her.

1193
01:47:28,782 --> 01:47:30,412
Can I eat a lot of onion?

1194
01:47:30,825 --> 01:47:32,535
-Sure.
-Let's have it together.

1195
01:47:32,619 --> 01:47:34,749
-Okay.
-Add a lot of onion please.

1196
01:47:35,580 --> 01:47:36,920
She likes onions.

1197
01:47:44,631 --> 01:47:46,681
Onion starts with an "o."

1198
01:47:51,388 --> 01:47:53,308
Stop showing off, rich boy.

1199
01:47:56,935 --> 01:47:58,595
ONION

1200
01:48:01,356 --> 01:48:03,226
Ms. Jang is kinder than I thought.

1201
01:48:03,316 --> 01:48:06,106
She is taking care of humans
around Mr. Koo as well.

1202
01:48:06,194 --> 01:48:08,244
Do you really think she is being kind?

1203
01:48:08,655 --> 01:48:11,485
Can you be kind to my boyfriend?

1204
01:48:12,617 --> 01:48:14,737
Why? Is your boyfriend mean?

1205
01:48:16,913 --> 01:48:17,913
Right.

1206
01:48:17,998 --> 01:48:21,248
My boyfriend is so mean and a total idiot.

1207
01:48:25,714 --> 01:48:27,384
Is Dr. Han all right?

1208
01:48:27,632 --> 01:48:29,342
-He isn't.
-I see.

1209
01:48:29,426 --> 01:48:30,886
He scares me to death every night.

1210
01:48:31,678 --> 01:48:34,308
He sang in his study last night.

1211
01:48:34,389 --> 01:48:35,389
What?

1212
01:48:43,189 --> 01:48:45,279
-You want to go in?
-Yes.

1213
01:48:45,358 --> 01:48:47,568
I need to find something
to report to Ms. Jang.

1214
01:48:47,819 --> 01:48:48,779
Listen to this.

1215
01:48:48,862 --> 01:48:51,072
Shall I pretend to be
a cute next-door neighbor

1216
01:48:51,156 --> 01:48:52,696
who's come to borrow a screwdriver?

1217
01:48:53,158 --> 01:48:55,658
No, don't you have other ideas?

1218
01:48:57,495 --> 01:48:58,905
There's something strange in this house.

1219
01:48:58,997 --> 01:49:00,037
What is it?

1220
01:49:01,958 --> 01:49:04,588
That's not a human, right?

1221
01:49:10,508 --> 01:49:13,468
Mi-ra borrowed my Qing Dynasty ceramic.

1222
01:49:13,553 --> 01:49:15,893
Well, she already took it
before I agreed to lend it, though.

1223
01:49:15,972 --> 01:49:17,352
Anyway, I let her borrow it.

1224
01:49:17,515 --> 01:49:19,885
She'll sell it and use all the money.
You won't get it back.

1225
01:49:20,268 --> 01:49:21,268
I'll get it back for you.

1226
01:49:21,352 --> 01:49:23,902
It's okay. If she doesn't return it,
I'll seize her salary.

1227
01:49:24,147 --> 01:49:25,687
You can't do it, but I can.

1228
01:49:28,193 --> 01:49:30,033
I should have seized her salary
or something

1229
01:49:30,111 --> 01:49:32,111
for all the money she took from me.

1230
01:49:33,531 --> 01:49:37,201
You said you won't stay for long
at that hotel, right?

1231
01:49:38,036 --> 01:49:39,946
Veronica's father recently

1232
01:49:40,038 --> 01:49:42,038
took over a hotel in Sydney.

1233
01:49:42,123 --> 01:49:44,333
Two of my father's restaurants will open
there.

1234
01:49:44,417 --> 01:49:45,457
It's a five-star hotel.

1235
01:49:45,585 --> 01:49:47,295
Would you like to work there?

1236
01:49:49,255 --> 01:49:51,215
I don't plan to leave this hotel.

1237
01:49:52,759 --> 01:49:56,599
Is there a special reason
why you have to stay at Man-wol's hotel?

1238
01:49:57,764 --> 01:50:00,854
You have a good career background,
and you enjoy showing off.

1239
01:50:00,934 --> 01:50:04,354
But it's a nameless hotel
without even a proper name card.

1240
01:50:04,437 --> 01:50:06,727
You are always working overtime there.

1241
01:50:07,107 --> 01:50:09,067
I find it very strange.

1242
01:50:09,943 --> 01:50:13,783
Sanchez, do you think I'd work
at an average hotel?

1243
01:50:15,115 --> 01:50:18,905
My hotel has world-class facilities.

1244
01:50:18,993 --> 01:50:20,253
You can't even imagine

1245
01:50:20,328 --> 01:50:22,708
how special the guests are.

1246
01:50:23,248 --> 01:50:25,078
There is only one shortcoming.

1247
01:50:25,166 --> 01:50:27,336
And that is I can't boast about it.

1248
01:50:30,463 --> 01:50:31,303
I see.

1249
01:50:31,381 --> 01:50:33,261
I thought you were working
for that crappy hotel

1250
01:50:33,341 --> 01:50:35,141
because you have feelings for Man-wol.

1251
01:50:35,218 --> 01:50:36,218
What?

1252
01:50:38,012 --> 01:50:39,762
I got you right on the spot.

1253
01:50:44,727 --> 01:50:47,517
You look like a pushover,
but you are cold.

1254
01:50:47,939 --> 01:50:50,189
-You seem slow, but you are sharp.
-Yes.

1255
01:50:50,441 --> 01:50:53,151
Right. It's just like how I look
like a pizza place owner,

1256
01:50:53,236 --> 01:50:55,236
but I'm a millionaire, right?

1257
01:50:55,363 --> 01:50:58,163
Veronica is now fully in love
with that side of me.

1258
01:50:58,449 --> 01:50:59,619
I'll get you more soda.

1259
01:50:59,951 --> 01:51:00,951
Okay.

1260
01:51:04,706 --> 01:51:06,116
LEE MI-RA

1261
01:51:10,879 --> 01:51:13,459
Did you sell Sanchez's ceramic?

1262
01:51:13,548 --> 01:51:14,668
Chan-sung.

1263
01:51:14,924 --> 01:51:18,224
Is there an available room
in your hotel right now?

1264
01:51:28,104 --> 01:51:30,324
I can't take a photo of a ghost
with my phone.

1265
01:51:35,778 --> 01:51:37,818
I can't take a picture of you either.

1266
01:51:39,532 --> 01:51:42,992
You can, if I let myself be seen
like I did at your school.

1267
01:51:43,077 --> 01:51:44,617
Although I can't do it for long.

1268
01:51:44,704 --> 01:51:45,544
Do it now.

1269
01:51:46,998 --> 01:51:48,668
Come on, let yourself be seen.

1270
01:51:51,336 --> 01:51:53,246
There you are.

1271
01:51:53,421 --> 01:51:54,421
I'm taking the picture now.

1272
01:51:56,549 --> 01:51:57,759
What are you guys doing here?

1273
01:51:59,636 --> 01:52:00,756
Mr. Koo?

1274
01:52:00,887 --> 01:52:01,967
What are you doing here?

1275
01:52:02,263 --> 01:52:05,983
We followed your doctor girlfriend.

1276
01:52:06,059 --> 01:52:07,059
Mi-ra?

1277
01:52:07,435 --> 01:52:08,435
Why?

1278
01:52:08,811 --> 01:52:10,101
I told them to.

1279
01:52:18,488 --> 01:52:20,868
Did you come to attach a ghost
to Mi-ra to torment her?

1280
01:52:20,949 --> 01:52:22,199
I thought you didn't care.

1281
01:52:22,283 --> 01:52:24,243
But you seem worried
I might do something to her.

1282
01:52:24,327 --> 01:52:26,367
Are you here to stand guard
over your girlfriend's house?

1283
01:52:26,996 --> 01:52:29,706
This is not her house.
It's her friend's house.

1284
01:52:30,667 --> 01:52:33,167
Mi-ra is staying with me.

1285
01:52:35,004 --> 01:52:36,134
At Sanchez's?

1286
01:52:39,217 --> 01:52:40,637
So you're living together.

1287
01:52:41,678 --> 01:52:44,598
Are you going to keep following her?
Do I have to keep guard?

1288
01:52:44,681 --> 01:52:47,521
I just wanted to know
what a good life she has.

1289
01:52:49,852 --> 01:52:50,942
Where are you going?

1290
01:52:51,604 --> 01:52:52,564
You have to take the ghost.

1291
01:52:52,647 --> 01:52:54,517
I didn't put it there.

1292
01:52:54,607 --> 01:52:57,187
I didn't even know
you were living with her.

1293
01:52:57,277 --> 01:53:00,027
If I had known,
I would've released 108 ghosts.

1294
01:53:00,113 --> 01:53:02,823
Either way, it means
there is a ghost in this house.

1295
01:53:02,907 --> 01:53:04,697
Let's take her to the hotel.

1296
01:53:06,786 --> 01:53:07,866
Ms. Jang.

1297
01:53:09,622 --> 01:53:10,672
Ms. Jang.

1298
01:53:10,748 --> 01:53:13,958
You only call me that
when you want something from me.

1299
01:53:18,798 --> 01:53:20,088
I heard from Mi-ra

1300
01:53:20,675 --> 01:53:22,755
that you keep hearing strange noises

1301
01:53:22,844 --> 01:53:24,014
and see strange things.

1302
01:53:24,095 --> 01:53:26,675
You want to stay at a hotel
for a while, right?

1303
01:53:26,764 --> 01:53:29,394
I got this house from my parents.
It's quite old,

1304
01:53:29,475 --> 01:53:32,395
so it's not properly soundproofed.
Maybe that's the reason.

1305
01:53:32,478 --> 01:53:34,858
I told him everything.

1306
01:53:35,273 --> 01:53:37,113
You can't even sleep after you moved in.

1307
01:53:38,609 --> 01:53:41,279
We could have just gone to your hotel.
You didn't have to come.

1308
01:53:41,612 --> 01:53:44,322
I came to see who the guest is.

1309
01:53:44,782 --> 01:53:47,702
We don't accept average guests.

1310
01:53:48,870 --> 01:53:50,870
Is that why your boss is with you?

1311
01:53:51,873 --> 01:53:52,873
Yes.

1312
01:53:53,082 --> 01:53:55,962
You can only come to our hotel
when you have Ms. Jang's invitation.

1313
01:53:56,461 --> 01:53:58,301
You have many doctors in your family.

1314
01:53:59,088 --> 01:54:01,588
Your hotel must run
on some sort of membership.

1315
01:54:02,175 --> 01:54:03,925
We just need an ordinary hotel.

1316
01:54:06,137 --> 01:54:07,427
Then you do that.

1317
01:54:09,515 --> 01:54:10,515
Excuse me.

1318
01:54:10,600 --> 01:54:12,770
Ms. Jang.

1319
01:54:13,144 --> 01:54:14,604
We have to take the guest to the hotel.

1320
01:54:14,687 --> 01:54:15,727
Forget it.

1321
01:54:15,855 --> 01:54:18,065
Why should I take care
of this house's ghost?

1322
01:54:18,149 --> 01:54:20,069
It's the house of my friend's friend.

1323
01:54:20,151 --> 01:54:23,611
I don't like your friend, and I don't
like you since you're her friend.

1324
01:54:31,829 --> 01:54:32,909
Is this the sound?

1325
01:54:32,997 --> 01:54:34,167
Do you hear it too?

1326
01:54:35,583 --> 01:54:36,963
We are not crazy, right?

1327
01:54:37,919 --> 01:54:40,379
We have a special service in our hotel.

1328
01:54:41,172 --> 01:54:42,382
You should get the service.

1329
01:54:55,311 --> 01:54:57,611
Her name is Gyeong-a
and she is dressed in retro style.

1330
01:54:57,688 --> 01:54:59,318
She is waiting for a doctor.

1331
01:54:59,857 --> 01:55:03,237
Could she be looking for
the dead father of this house?

1332
01:55:03,778 --> 01:55:04,778
Maybe.

1333
01:55:04,862 --> 01:55:06,952
If she sees you, she might run away.

1334
01:55:07,323 --> 01:55:08,533
I will go in first.

1335
01:55:10,535 --> 01:55:11,615
Aren't you scared?

1336
01:55:13,204 --> 01:55:14,414
No, I have you.

1337
01:55:38,187 --> 01:55:39,267
Gyeong-a?

1338
01:55:41,232 --> 01:55:42,282
Min?

1339
01:55:47,572 --> 01:55:48,612
Min.

1340
01:55:53,035 --> 01:55:53,995
I'm all right.

1341
01:55:55,496 --> 01:55:58,036
Min, you came back.

1342
01:55:58,249 --> 01:55:59,249
Min.

1343
01:56:00,084 --> 01:56:02,254
Who is Min?

1344
01:56:16,726 --> 01:56:18,636
I'm sorry I hurt you.

1345
01:56:21,898 --> 01:56:23,518
But my heart

1346
01:56:24,066 --> 01:56:26,106
already belongs to the doctor.

1347
01:56:26,694 --> 01:56:30,324
So, Min and the doctor are
different people.

1348
01:56:33,201 --> 01:56:34,331
Are you sick?

1349
01:56:35,369 --> 01:56:38,999
Min, I don't have a lot of time.

1350
01:56:39,290 --> 01:56:41,250
I can't share that time with you.

1351
01:56:41,542 --> 01:56:44,382
But I'll let you give me a goodbye kiss.

1352
01:56:51,093 --> 01:56:53,723
Gyeong-a, is this your diary?

1353
01:56:55,223 --> 01:56:57,183
Suk-hui, stop it!

1354
01:56:58,601 --> 01:57:00,271
Don't touch my things!

1355
01:57:00,895 --> 01:57:02,475
I must be Suk-hui.

1356
01:57:04,190 --> 01:57:06,440
It's not my fault
you couldn't win Min's heart.

1357
01:57:06,901 --> 01:57:09,031
Stop your mean jealousy.

1358
01:57:10,780 --> 01:57:12,990
What are all these postcards and letters?

1359
01:57:19,080 --> 01:57:20,920
Min, you ask her.

1360
01:57:24,961 --> 01:57:27,421
Gyeong-a, what are all these postcards?

1361
01:57:30,299 --> 01:57:34,009
I'm very weak, so I can't go outside.

1362
01:57:34,095 --> 01:57:35,295
And I don't have any friends.

1363
01:57:35,388 --> 01:57:37,218
So I sent my story to a radio station,

1364
01:57:37,306 --> 01:57:39,636
and all these people
sent me postcards wishing me well.

1365
01:57:44,772 --> 01:57:46,322
"I hope you recover soon.

1366
01:57:46,399 --> 01:57:48,229
I also wish you good luck
with your romance.

1367
01:57:48,609 --> 01:57:51,359
From Hui, an avid listener
from Ssangmun-dong

1368
01:57:51,445 --> 01:57:53,105
who's also lovestruck just like you."

1369
01:57:54,240 --> 01:57:55,370
This is actually real.

1370
01:57:58,411 --> 01:57:59,791
Hyeok must be here.

1371
01:58:07,253 --> 01:58:08,593
There must be someone named Hyeok.

1372
01:58:09,130 --> 01:58:12,340
Judging from the look on her face,
Hyeok must like her as well.

1373
01:58:14,051 --> 01:58:18,811
So that means Hyeok, Min,
and the doctor all like Gyeong-a

1374
01:58:18,889 --> 01:58:20,219
except for Suk-hui.

1375
01:58:20,308 --> 01:58:22,808
I guess Suk-hui is the only villain here.

1376
01:58:23,019 --> 01:58:24,729
I'll keep pretending I'm Min.

1377
01:58:24,812 --> 01:58:26,612
And we should take her to the hotel.

1378
01:58:27,773 --> 01:58:30,153
Gyeong-a can't be a guest at our hotel...

1379
01:58:32,111 --> 01:58:35,531
because she isn't a soul of a human being.

1380
01:58:51,005 --> 01:58:52,375
She's not a ghost then?

1381
01:58:52,715 --> 01:58:56,635
Didn't you feel something weird
when she hugged you earlier?

1382
01:58:57,803 --> 01:58:59,723
Come to think of it,
I didn't feel cold at all.

1383
01:58:59,805 --> 01:59:02,765
I always felt a chill every time
I touched a ghost at our hotel.

1384
01:59:03,100 --> 01:59:04,640
But that wasn't the case with Gyeong-a.

1385
01:59:05,019 --> 01:59:07,439
That's an imaginary soul
that was created by a human.

1386
01:59:08,272 --> 01:59:09,442
"An imaginary soul"?

1387
01:59:09,982 --> 01:59:11,402
Yes, it's imaginary.

1388
01:59:12,735 --> 01:59:16,695
Gyeong-a was created
in someone's imagination.

1389
01:59:17,698 --> 01:59:20,078
Someone created her?

1390
01:59:20,993 --> 01:59:22,623
She had an incurable illness,

1391
01:59:22,703 --> 01:59:25,213
was loved by Hyeok and Min,

1392
01:59:25,289 --> 01:59:27,669
and she even had a love affair
with a doctor.

1393
01:59:28,167 --> 01:59:31,247
The diary is real, and someone did send
a story to the radio station.

1394
01:59:31,337 --> 01:59:33,587
But the problem is
that it wasn't Gyeong-a.

1395
01:59:33,673 --> 01:59:36,473
They were done by the human
who created her.

1396
01:59:38,886 --> 01:59:39,846
Who could that be?

1397
01:59:39,929 --> 01:59:42,679
If we find that person,
we can get rid of Gyeong-a.

1398
01:59:43,974 --> 01:59:47,814
Who is this delusional person
that's so immersed in this sad love story?

1399
01:59:48,437 --> 01:59:49,647
What's wrong with you guys?

1400
01:59:49,730 --> 01:59:52,150
-Mother, they're here to help us.
-Please leave.

1401
01:59:52,233 --> 01:59:54,613
-What's going on?
-Mother, wait.

1402
01:59:58,280 --> 02:00:00,530
What are you doing in my study?

1403
02:00:01,117 --> 02:00:02,787
Everything here belongs to me.

1404
02:00:06,664 --> 02:00:07,674
I see.

1405
02:00:13,671 --> 02:00:15,631
May I ask your name, ma'am?

1406
02:00:16,841 --> 02:00:18,181
Lee Bok-hui.

1407
02:00:20,594 --> 02:00:22,144
You should wait downstairs.

1408
02:00:30,813 --> 02:00:33,153
Do you know a lady named Gyeong-a?

1409
02:00:42,116 --> 02:00:44,906
I'm Gyeong-a.

1410
02:00:57,673 --> 02:00:59,383
I married my husband

1411
02:01:00,301 --> 02:01:03,011
when I was 22
through an arranged marriage.

1412
02:01:04,597 --> 02:01:06,717
I never got to date anyone.

1413
02:01:07,933 --> 02:01:09,393
And that's when...

1414
02:01:12,897 --> 02:01:14,227
I created Gyeong-a.

1415
02:01:15,399 --> 02:01:18,189
I was so happy to be able to experience

1416
02:01:18,277 --> 02:01:21,857
a pure, affectionate,
and passionate love as Gyeong-a,

1417
02:01:22,448 --> 02:01:26,238
just like my favorite movie character.

1418
02:01:26,327 --> 02:01:30,457
The strong imaginary soul you created
still exists.

1419
02:01:31,999 --> 02:01:33,499
It's like an old movie.

1420
02:01:35,169 --> 02:01:36,339
I see.

1421
02:01:37,713 --> 02:01:39,303
You don't seem startled.

1422
02:01:39,381 --> 02:01:42,551
If you live for this long,
you don't get startled that easily.

1423
02:01:42,635 --> 02:01:43,585
On top of that,

1424
02:01:43,677 --> 02:01:46,257
I was once so delusional
that I created Gyeong-a.

1425
02:01:48,057 --> 02:01:50,937
Gyeong-a called me Min.

1426
02:01:51,101 --> 02:01:52,601
You look just like him.

1427
02:01:53,062 --> 02:01:55,812
She actually liked Min the most.

1428
02:01:58,150 --> 02:01:59,860
What about the doctor?

1429
02:02:00,069 --> 02:02:02,529
She must've been a huge flirt.

1430
02:02:04,365 --> 02:02:07,275
Do I need to get rid of Gyeong-a?

1431
02:02:08,077 --> 02:02:10,367
Your son and wife are suffering
because of her.

1432
02:02:13,374 --> 02:02:14,464
I see.

1433
02:02:15,417 --> 02:02:19,757
I was able to forget about Gyeong-a
thanks to my son.

1434
02:02:41,944 --> 02:02:45,204
She got married to a stranger
whom she didn't love.

1435
02:02:45,281 --> 02:02:46,411
It must've been hard for her.

1436
02:02:47,950 --> 02:02:49,330
Whether it was imaginary or delusional,

1437
02:02:50,119 --> 02:02:53,039
I'm sure it still helped her cope
with her situation.

1438
02:02:54,873 --> 02:02:58,173
Changing one's reality
by creating an imaginary soul...

1439
02:03:00,462 --> 02:03:01,842
That's a good idea.

1440
02:03:04,133 --> 02:03:07,263
She asked us to join her for dinner.
What should we do?

1441
02:03:07,344 --> 02:03:09,684
She said goodbye to Gyeong-a,
so she must feel lonely.

1442
02:03:09,763 --> 02:03:11,933
So you stay as Min
and console her over dinner.

1443
02:03:12,016 --> 02:03:13,926
Suk-hui is a villain,
so I'm going to leave.

1444
02:03:15,269 --> 02:03:16,229
Okay, then.

1445
02:03:21,483 --> 02:03:22,693
It's burning beautifully.

1446
02:03:25,279 --> 02:03:26,319
You're right.

1447
02:03:29,450 --> 02:03:30,530
It's beautiful.

1448
02:03:37,583 --> 02:03:40,843
Ma'am, you don't need to prepare
too many dishes.

1449
02:03:42,463 --> 02:03:44,843
Min, just wait here quietly.

1450
02:03:49,303 --> 02:03:50,353
Excuse me.

1451
02:03:51,138 --> 02:03:52,598
Did Mi-ra leave?

1452
02:03:52,681 --> 02:03:54,561
Yes, she probably went back
to the hospital.

1453
02:03:55,684 --> 02:03:59,024
By the way, thank you
for inviting us to the hotel.

1454
02:03:59,647 --> 02:04:00,557
Pardon?

1455
02:04:00,648 --> 02:04:04,028
Your boss gave us invitations
to the hotel.

1456
02:04:04,735 --> 02:04:05,895
Invitations?

1457
02:04:06,111 --> 02:04:08,321
We'll make sure we visit. I can't wait.

1458
02:04:09,615 --> 02:04:13,445
By any chance, did she give
an invitation to Mi-ra as well?

1459
02:04:22,586 --> 02:04:24,666
I didn't know there was a hotel here.

1460
02:04:25,506 --> 02:04:27,546
Chan-sung is working
at an incredible hotel.

1461
02:04:40,938 --> 02:04:42,188
Welcome.

1462
02:04:42,356 --> 02:04:43,936
Ms. Jang is waiting for you.

1463
02:04:44,108 --> 02:04:45,478
Oh, thank you.

1464
02:04:45,567 --> 02:04:46,567
This way.

1465
02:05:01,250 --> 02:05:02,330
Please follow me.

1466
02:05:02,418 --> 02:05:06,208
Ms. Jang prepared something very special
for you. Let me take you there.

1467
02:05:06,422 --> 02:05:08,132
This hotel is amazing.

1468
02:05:33,949 --> 02:05:35,119
Welcome.

1469
02:05:36,076 --> 02:05:39,246
Welcome to Hotel del Luna.

1470
02:05:39,830 --> 02:05:41,620
Thank you for inviting me.

1471
02:05:42,833 --> 02:05:43,923
The pleasure's mine.

1472
02:05:44,209 --> 02:05:45,419
I just couldn't...

1473
02:05:46,837 --> 02:05:50,547
let you pass by.

1474
02:05:54,887 --> 02:05:56,257
This place is really nice.

1475
02:06:00,267 --> 02:06:02,437
But why is this place empty?

1476
02:06:03,395 --> 02:06:05,055
It's not empty.

1477
02:06:05,481 --> 02:06:07,481
You just can't see anything

1478
02:06:09,276 --> 02:06:10,316
because of that.

1479
02:06:17,493 --> 02:06:18,583
This?

1480
02:06:18,660 --> 02:06:20,620
You can't see them because of that.

1481
02:06:21,580 --> 02:06:24,460
Earlier, you couldn't hear
anything either.

1482
02:06:27,294 --> 02:06:28,384
Is this the sound?

1483
02:06:28,462 --> 02:06:29,632
We're not crazy, right?

1484
02:06:42,267 --> 02:06:45,307
If I take this off,
will I be able to see some other things?

1485
02:06:55,447 --> 02:06:57,407
Why don't you let me hold onto it for you?

1486
02:08:36,673 --> 02:08:38,013
Do you like it?

1487
02:08:39,176 --> 02:08:42,546
Yes, I love amusement parks.

1488
02:08:42,846 --> 02:08:45,056
Is that so? I thought so too.

1489
02:08:47,684 --> 02:08:49,444
You seem happy in the photo.

1490
02:08:55,275 --> 02:08:56,685
You found this.

1491
02:08:57,402 --> 02:08:58,702
Thank you.

1492
02:08:59,780 --> 02:09:01,410
When I was young,

1493
02:09:02,324 --> 02:09:05,244
I went to the amusement park
with my family and took this photo.

1494
02:09:05,744 --> 02:09:06,834
That's right.

1495
02:09:12,751 --> 02:09:16,631
You from that day are standing over there.

1496
02:09:21,677 --> 02:09:23,797
They're my parents and my sister.

1497
02:09:25,555 --> 02:09:26,765
I'm happy.

1498
02:09:27,391 --> 02:09:28,481
I really hate

1499
02:09:29,309 --> 02:09:31,519
that you are

1500
02:09:32,437 --> 02:09:33,687
happy.

1501
02:09:36,483 --> 02:09:37,613
That's why

1502
02:09:39,111 --> 02:09:42,071
I'm going to breathe sadness
into that girl.

1503
02:09:44,408 --> 02:09:46,738
And I'll give her to you as a gift.

1504
02:10:24,906 --> 02:10:25,946
Hello.

1505
02:10:30,537 --> 02:10:33,207
You don't have a happy family.

1506
02:10:33,707 --> 02:10:36,587
Your mother said this to you all the time.

1507
02:10:39,171 --> 02:10:42,631
"You should have never been born.
I regret giving birth to you."

1508
02:10:42,924 --> 02:10:45,094
Your dad got angry whenever he saw you.

1509
02:10:45,177 --> 02:10:48,257
"Nothing is working out
all because of you, you witch."

1510
02:10:49,514 --> 02:10:51,644
After your annoying sister was born,

1511
02:10:51,808 --> 02:10:54,188
your parents loved only her.

1512
02:10:55,312 --> 02:10:58,652
Look at this.
The day you came to the amusement park,

1513
02:10:59,024 --> 02:11:02,154
your family left you here and went home.

1514
02:11:06,740 --> 02:11:09,530
It was the saddest day of your life.

1515
02:11:16,958 --> 02:11:21,708
Mom. Dad. Don't abandon me.

1516
02:11:38,355 --> 02:11:41,185
All right. Go.

1517
02:11:42,192 --> 02:11:45,822
Go to her and fill every day of her life

1518
02:11:46,279 --> 02:11:50,199
with sad memories of a girl
who should've never been born.

1519
02:13:12,199 --> 02:13:13,739
Thank you, Chan-sung.

1520
02:13:14,951 --> 02:13:16,621
Thanks to you, I got to meet her.

1521
02:13:17,537 --> 02:13:19,827
And thanks to you, I've found a great way.

1522
02:13:21,374 --> 02:13:22,584
So...

1523
02:13:24,336 --> 02:13:26,046
I was able to resolve my grudge a bit.

1524
02:13:26,630 --> 02:13:27,710
Don't do it.

1525
02:13:28,298 --> 02:13:29,718
I already did.

1526
02:13:32,219 --> 02:13:33,259
This is...

1527
02:13:34,179 --> 02:13:38,389
way stronger than
the imaginary soul Bok-hui created.

1528
02:13:40,060 --> 02:13:41,770
Because I created it.

1529
02:13:46,525 --> 02:13:48,235
It's a curse.

1530
02:14:12,968 --> 02:14:15,548
-Stop it.
-You can't stand it?

1531
02:14:16,930 --> 02:14:19,100
Then run away from me, Chan-sung.

1532
02:14:19,516 --> 02:14:20,676
I'll let you go.

1533
02:14:25,689 --> 02:14:26,729
I won't.

1534
02:14:28,441 --> 02:14:29,691
Protect me.

1535
02:15:00,140 --> 02:15:02,730
Chan-sung, let her go.

1536
02:15:25,165 --> 02:15:26,825
Whatever it is you're going to do,

1537
02:15:27,667 --> 02:15:28,997
just don't forget this.

1538
02:15:30,629 --> 02:15:34,049
I don't care if this is
your prison or your fence.

1539
02:15:35,884 --> 02:15:36,894
I will...

1540
02:15:38,094 --> 02:15:39,604
stay here with you.

1541
02:15:54,694 --> 02:15:55,904
Aren't you scared?

1542
02:15:58,198 --> 02:15:59,528
No, I have you.

1543
02:16:32,148 --> 02:16:33,398
You woke up.

1544
02:16:34,818 --> 02:16:35,938
Who are you?

1545
02:16:36,027 --> 02:16:39,607
Ms. Jang asked me to take you home
because you were too drunk.

1546
02:16:39,864 --> 02:16:41,284
I was drunk?

1547
02:16:41,366 --> 02:16:43,616
Yes. The hospital is
in Myeongnyun-dong, right?

1548
02:16:44,035 --> 02:16:46,035
-Sir, let's get going.
-Sure.

1549
02:17:44,512 --> 02:17:46,392
Everything will be okay now.

1550
02:17:49,517 --> 02:17:51,517
You ruined everything.

1551
02:18:06,493 --> 02:18:07,953
I really don't know.

1552
02:18:08,787 --> 02:18:10,617
When I saw you in my dream,

1553
02:18:12,207 --> 02:18:13,877
you were just in love.

1554
02:18:20,465 --> 02:18:23,255
This is the last time we'll look
at this scenery together.

1555
02:18:23,551 --> 02:18:24,931
I'm leaving with my people.

1556
02:18:26,137 --> 02:18:28,307
Are you planning to join the rebellion?

1557
02:18:30,433 --> 02:18:32,523
They wish to set this country right.

1558
02:18:32,811 --> 02:18:35,441
It's much better than living
as a thief here and getting caught

1559
02:18:36,397 --> 02:18:37,767
and killed eventually.

1560
02:18:38,483 --> 02:18:39,613
Come to the palace.

1561
02:18:41,027 --> 02:18:42,607
I can keep you safe.

1562
02:18:55,917 --> 02:18:58,337
Are you telling me
to desert my people and go to you?

1563
02:19:03,758 --> 02:19:04,838
I can't.

1564
02:19:06,886 --> 02:19:08,556
Then shall I go to you?

1565
02:19:19,732 --> 02:19:23,282
If you beg me to come,
I will risk my life and go with you.

1566
02:19:26,906 --> 02:19:28,026
Don't.

1567
02:19:30,159 --> 02:19:31,999
There is no way

1568
02:19:33,496 --> 02:19:34,656
we can be together.

1569
02:19:43,631 --> 02:19:44,761
Right.

1570
02:19:48,803 --> 02:19:50,933
I suppose I won't need
to come here ever again.

1571
02:19:56,185 --> 02:19:57,935
You were a great drinking buddy,

1572
02:20:00,106 --> 02:20:01,316
so I will miss you.

1573
02:21:31,280 --> 02:21:33,830
Everyone's ready. When should we leave?

1574
02:21:34,450 --> 02:21:35,740
He was here.

1575
02:21:36,703 --> 02:21:38,293
He's probably there now.

1576
02:21:39,455 --> 02:21:41,325
Let me go see him for one last time.

1577
02:21:42,583 --> 02:21:43,633
Man-wol.

1578
02:21:45,086 --> 02:21:46,296
Will you come back?

1579
02:21:46,546 --> 02:21:49,586
Yes. Of course, I'll be back.

1580
02:22:00,685 --> 02:22:02,265
You don't need to come back.

1581
02:22:03,146 --> 02:22:04,686
I'll be fine either way,

1582
02:22:05,314 --> 02:22:06,734
so do as you wish.

1583
02:22:07,316 --> 02:22:08,526
No, I will come back.

1584
02:22:09,819 --> 02:22:11,359
Let me see him just once more.

1585
02:22:13,239 --> 02:22:14,569
Wait for me.

1586
02:23:22,266 --> 02:23:25,346
All of your people will die
because of you.

1587
02:24:43,556 --> 02:24:45,346
Thanks to you,
I made a great contribution.

1588
02:24:59,113 --> 02:25:00,993
You were the one who took me there

1589
02:25:02,783 --> 02:25:05,413
and bought me enough time.
It's all thanks to you.

1590
02:25:06,996 --> 02:25:08,536
Hence, I will spare your life.

1591
02:25:09,624 --> 02:25:11,084
I will kill you.

1592
02:25:12,293 --> 02:25:14,093
I will kill you...

1593
02:25:15,588 --> 02:25:17,008
at all costs.

1594
02:25:19,217 --> 02:25:20,507
If you wish to kill me,

1595
02:25:22,595 --> 02:25:24,345
you will have to stay alive.

1596
02:26:53,102 --> 02:26:54,102
Yeon-u...

1597
02:26:54,478 --> 02:26:55,558
Yeon-u.

1598
02:26:56,647 --> 02:26:58,727
Yeon-u!

1599
02:26:59,025 --> 02:27:02,315
No, Yeon-u.

1600
02:27:03,321 --> 02:27:04,361
Let go of me!

1601
02:27:05,990 --> 02:27:12,410
Yeon-u.

1602
02:27:13,039 --> 02:27:14,459
Yeon-u!

1603
02:27:16,083 --> 02:27:17,423
Yeon-u.

1604
02:27:20,588 --> 02:27:21,628
Yeon-u.

1605
02:28:06,634 --> 02:28:09,354
Since you helped the general
make a great contribution,

1606
02:28:09,428 --> 02:28:11,428
I will show mercy on you.

1607
02:28:34,537 --> 02:28:36,117
FULL MOON

1608
02:29:17,913 --> 02:29:19,673
I will kill you

1609
02:29:20,416 --> 02:29:21,826
at all costs.

1610
02:30:38,536 --> 02:30:39,536
Chan-sung.

1611
02:30:46,460 --> 02:30:47,500
Are you all right?

1612
02:30:49,797 --> 02:30:50,837
What happened?

1613
02:30:50,923 --> 02:30:52,843
Man-wol brought you home.

1614
02:30:53,467 --> 02:30:55,297
And you've been sleeping for several days.

1615
02:30:55,386 --> 02:30:57,636
"Several days"? What do you mean?

1616
02:30:57,721 --> 02:30:59,601
You've been sleeping
for three days straight.

1617
02:31:07,982 --> 02:31:09,322
Why is that painting here?

1618
02:31:09,858 --> 02:31:11,358
Man-wol left it here.

1619
02:31:12,695 --> 02:31:13,605
That...

1620
02:31:13,696 --> 02:31:15,946
She said it was taking up space,
so she left it here.

1621
02:31:16,865 --> 02:31:18,485
By the way, is she going somewhere?

1622
02:32:09,126 --> 02:32:13,086
Wherever she goes,
the Moon Tree will put down roots there.

1623
02:32:13,213 --> 02:32:16,263
And there stands
the Guest House of the Moon.

1624
02:32:19,345 --> 02:32:20,675
She's gone.

1625
02:32:59,885 --> 02:33:04,215
When you see me off, don't feel lonely.

1626
02:33:21,782 --> 02:33:22,952
Whether...

1627
02:33:25,744 --> 02:33:27,584
this place is a fence

1628
02:33:28,580 --> 02:33:29,870
or prison for me...

1629
02:33:34,044 --> 02:33:36,094
what I have is hell.

1630
02:33:40,718 --> 02:33:42,798
It's not that wonderful...

1631
02:33:46,849 --> 02:33:48,479
to be in hell together.

1632
02:34:00,446 --> 02:34:01,446
Goodbye.

1633
02:34:04,616 --> 02:34:05,866
Chan-sung.

1634
02:35:22,319 --> 02:35:24,399
Subtitle translation by Wayne Ryu
